            }

    };
function X5() {

        s,

        n = "";
    for (; t < arguments.length;)

const $E = t => {

        return t;

        r = "";
    for (let n = 0; n < t.length; n++)

    return r
};
function J5(t, ...s) {

        i = o;

            return d;

        return a(c, u), u
    }

    }

const Np = .21;
function qE(t) {
    return t * (1 + Np)
}
function ft(t, s=!0) {
    if (t == null || t === "")
        return "0,00 €";
    let r;
    return typeof t == "string" ? r = parseFloat(t.replace(",", ".")) : r = t, isNaN(r) || r < 0 ? "0,00 €" : (s && (r = qE(r)), new Intl.NumberFormat("es-ES", {
        style: "currency",
        currency: "EUR",
        minimumFractionDigits: 2
    }).format(r))
}
function yL(t) {
    if (t == null || t === "")
        return {
            basePrice: "0,00 €",
            iva: "0,00 €",
            totalPrice: "0,00 €",
            basePriceNum: 0,
            ivaNum: 0,
            totalPriceNum: 0
        };
    let s;
    if (typeof t == "string" ? s = parseFloat(t.replace(",", ".")) : s = t, isNaN(s) || s < 0)
        return {
            basePrice: "0,00 €",
            iva: "0,00 €",
            totalPrice: "0,00 €",
            basePriceNum: 0,
            ivaNum: 0,
            totalPriceNum: 0
        };
    const r = s * Np,
        n = s + r;
    return {
        basePrice: new Intl.NumberFormat("es-ES", {
            style: "currency",
            currency: "EUR",
            minimumFractionDigits: 2
        }).format(s),
        iva: new Intl.NumberFormat("es-ES", {
            style: "currency",
            currency: "EUR",
            minimumFractionDigits: 2
        }).format(r),
        totalPrice: new Intl.NumberFormat("es-ES", {
            style: "currency",
            currency: "EUR",
            minimumFractionDigits: 2
        }).format(n),
        basePriceNum: s,
        ivaNum: r,
        totalPriceNum: n
    }
}
function jL(t) {
    if (t == null || t === "")
        return "N/A";
    const s = typeof t == "string" ? parseFloat(t) : t;
    return isNaN(s) || s <= 0 ? "N/A" : `${(s / 100).toFixed(2)} kg`
}
function bL(t) {

    }).format(s)
}

const PL = ["top", "right", "bottom", "left"],
    ho = Math.min,
    sn = Math.max,
    vf = Math.round,
    sh = Math.floor,
    wa = t => ({
        x: t,
        y: t
    }),
    _L = {
        left: "right",
        right: "left",
        bottom: "top",
        top: "bottom"
    },
    TL = {
        start: "end",
        end: "start"
    };
function kv(t, s, r) {
    return sn(t, ho(s, r))
}
function vi(t, s) {
    return typeof t == "function" ? t(s) : t
}
function yi(t) {
    return t.split("-")[0]
}
function ed(t) {
    return t.split("-")[1]
}
function Lj(t) {
    return t === "x" ? "y" : "x"
}
function Fj(t) {
    return t === "y" ? "height" : "width"
}
function fo(t) {
    return ["top", "bottom"].includes(yi(t)) ? "y" : "x"
}
function zj(t) {
    return Lj(fo(t))
}
function AL(t, s, r) {
    r === void 0 && (r = !1);
    const n = ed(t),
        a = zj(t),
        i = Fj(a);
    let o = a === "x" ? n === (r ? "end" : "start") ? "right" : "left" : n === "start" ? "bottom" : "top";
    return s.reference[i] > s.floating[i] && (o = yf(o)), [o, yf(o)]
}
function ML(t) {
    const s = yf(t);
    return [Pv(t), s, Pv(s)]
}
function Pv(t) {
    return t.replace(/start|end/g, s => TL[s])
}
function RL(t, s, r) {
    const n = ["left", "right"],
        a = ["right", "left"],
        i = ["top", "bottom"],
        o = ["bottom", "top"];
    switch (t) {
    case "top":
    case "bottom":
        return r ? s ? a : n : s ? n : a;
    case "left":
    case "right":
        return s ? i : o;
    default:
        return []
    }
}
function IL(t, s, r, n) {
    const a = ed(t);
    let i = RL(yi(t), r === "start", n);
    return a && (i = i.map(o => o + "-" + a), s && (i = i.concat(i.map(Pv)))), i
}
function yf(t) {
    return t.replace(/left|right|bottom|top/g, s => _L[s])
}
function DL(t) {
    return {
        top: 0,
        right: 0,
        bottom: 0,
        left: 0,
        ...t
    }
}
function YE(t) {
    return typeof t != "number" ? DL(t) : {
        top: t,
        right: t,
        bottom: t,
        left: t
    }
}
function jf(t) {
    const {x: s, y: r, width: n, height: a} = t;
    return {
        width: n,
        height: a,
        top: r,
        left: s,
        right: s + n,
        bottom: r + a,
        x: s,
        y: r
    }
}
function lw(t, s, r) {
    let {reference: n, floating: a} = t;
    const i = fo(s),
        o = zj(s),
        l = Fj(o),
        c = yi(s),
        d = i === "y",
        u = n.x + n.width / 2 - a.width / 2,
        m = n.y + n.height / 2 - a.height / 2,
        f = n[l] / 2 - a[l] / 2;
    let y;
    switch (c) {
    case "top":
        y = {
            x: u,
            y: n.y - a.height
        };
        break;
    case "bottom":
        y = {
            x: u,
            y: n.y + n.height
        };
        break;
    case "right":
        y = {
            x: n.x + n.width,
            y: m
        };
        break;
    case "left":
        y = {
            x: n.x - a.width,
            y: m
        };
        break;
    default:
        y = {
            x: n.x,
            y: n.y
        }
    }
    switch (ed(s)) {
    case "start":
        y[o] -= f * (r && d ? -1 : 1);
        break;
    case "end":
        y[o] += f * (r && d ? -1 : 1);
        break
    }
    return y
}
const OL = async (t, s, r) => {
    const {placement: n="bottom", strategy: a="absolute", middleware: i=[], platform: o} = r,
        l = i.filter(Boolean),
        c = await (o.isRTL == null ? void 0 : o.isRTL(s));
    let d = await o.getElementRects({
            reference: t,
            floating: s,
            strategy: a
        }),
        {x: u, y: m} = lw(d, n, c),
        f = n,
        y = {},
        g = 0;
    for (let x = 0; x < l.length; x++) {
        const {name: j, fn: b} = l[x],
            {x: p, y: v, data: N, reset: w} = await b({
                x: u,
                y: m,
                initialPlacement: n,
                placement: f,
                strategy: a,
                middlewareData: y,
                rects: d,
                platform: o,
                elements: {
                    reference: t,
                    floating: s
                }
            });
        u = p ?? u,
        m = v ?? m,
        y = {
            ...y,
            [j]: {
                ...y[j],
                ...N
            }
        },
        w && g <= 50 && (g++, typeof w == "object" && (w.placement && (f = w.placement), w.rects && (d = w.rects === !0 ? await o.getElementRects({
            reference: t,
            floating: s,
            strategy: a
        }) : w.rects), {x: u, y: m} = lw(d, f, c)), x = -1)
    }
    return {
        x: u,
        y: m,
        placement: f,
        strategy: a,
        middlewareData: y
    }
};
async function bu(t, s) {
    var r;
    s === void 0 && (s = {});
    const {x: n, y: a, platform: i, rects: o, elements: l, strategy: c} = t,
        {boundary: d="clippingAncestors", rootBoundary: u="viewport", elementContext: m="floating", altBoundary: f=!1, padding: y=0} = vi(s, t),
        g = YE(y),
        j = l[f ? m === "floating" ? "reference" : "floating" : m],
        b = jf(await i.getClippingRect({
            element: (r = await (i.isElement == null ? void 0 : i.isElement(j))) == null || r ? j : j.contextElement || await (i.getDocumentElement == null ? void 0 : i.getDocumentElement(l.floating)),
            boundary: d,
            rootBoundary: u,
            strategy: c
        })),
        p = m === "floating" ? {
            x: n,
            y: a,
            width: o.floating.width,
            height: o.floating.height
        } : o.reference,
        v = await (i.getOffsetParent == null ? void 0 : i.getOffsetParent(l.floating)),
        N = await (i.isElement == null ? void 0 : i.isElement(v)) ? await (i.getScale == null ? void 0 : i.getScale(v)) || {
            x: 1,
            y: 1
        } : {
            x: 1,
            y: 1
        },
        w = jf(i.convertOffsetParentRelativeRectToViewportRelativeRect ? await i.convertOffsetParentRelativeRectToViewportRelativeRect({
            elements: l,
            rect: p,
            offsetParent: v,
            strategy: c
        }) : p);
    return {
        top: (b.top - w.top + g.top) / N.y,
        bottom: (w.bottom - b.bottom + g.bottom) / N.y,
        left: (b.left - w.left + g.left) / N.x,
        right: (w.right - b.right + g.right) / N.x
    }
}

function cw(t, s) {
    return {
        top: t.top - s.height,
        right: t.right - s.width,
        bottom: t.bottom - s.height,
        left: t.left - s.width
    }
}
function dw(t) {

function wp() {
    return typeof window < "u"
}
function td(t) {
    return QE(t) ? (t.nodeName || "").toLowerCase() : "#document"
}
function dn(t) {
    var s;
    return (t == null || (s = t.ownerDocument) == null ? void 0 : s.defaultView) || window
}
function Ra(t) {
    var s;
    return (s = (QE(t) ? t.ownerDocument : t.document) || window.document) == null ? void 0 : s.documentElement
}
function QE(t) {
    return wp() ? t instanceof Node || t instanceof dn(t).Node : !1
}
function Jn(t) {
    return wp() ? t instanceof Element || t instanceof dn(t).Element : !1
}
function Pa(t) {
    return wp() ? t instanceof HTMLElement || t instanceof dn(t).HTMLElement : !1
}
function uw(t) {
    return !wp() || typeof ShadowRoot > "u" ? !1 : t instanceof ShadowRoot || t instanceof dn(t).ShadowRoot
}
function cm(t) {
    const {overflow: s, overflowX: r, overflowY: n, display: a} = ea(t);
    return /auto|scroll|overlay|hidden|clip/.test(s + n + r) && !["inline", "contents"].includes(a)
}
function HL(t) {
    return ["table", "td", "th"].includes(td(t))
}
function Cp(t) {
    return [":popover-open", ":modal"].some(s => {
        try {
            return t.matches(s)
        } catch {
            return !1
        }
    })
}
function $j(t) {
    const s = Vj(),
        r = Jn(t) ? ea(t) : t;
    return ["transform", "translate", "scale", "rotate", "perspective"].some(n => r[n] ? r[n] !== "none" : !1) || (r.containerType ? r.containerType !== "normal" : !1) || !s && (r.backdropFilter ? r.backdropFilter !== "none" : !1) || !s && (r.filter ? r.filter !== "none" : !1) || ["transform", "translate", "scale", "rotate", "perspective", "filter"].some(n => (r.willChange || "").includes(n)) || ["paint", "layout", "strict", "content"].some(n => (r.contain || "").includes(n))
}
function WL(t) {
    let s = po(t);
    for (; Pa(s) && !Ac(s);) {
        if ($j(s))
            return s;
        if (Cp(s))
            return null;
        s = po(s)
    }
    return null
}
function Vj() {
    return typeof CSS > "u" || !CSS.supports ? !1 : CSS.supports("-webkit-backdrop-filter", "none")
}
function Ac(t) {
    return ["html", "body", "#document"].includes(td(t))
}
function ea(t) {
    return dn(t).getComputedStyle(t)
}
function Sp(t) {
    return Jn(t) ? {
        scrollLeft: t.scrollLeft,
        scrollTop: t.scrollTop
    } : {
        scrollLeft: t.scrollX,
        scrollTop: t.scrollY
    }
}
function po(t) {
    if (td(t) === "html")
        return t;
    const s = t.assignedSlot || t.parentNode || uw(t) && t.host || Ra(t);
    return uw(s) ? s.host : s
}
function ZE(t) {
    const s = po(t);
    return Ac(s) ? t.ownerDocument ? t.ownerDocument.body : t.body : Pa(s) && cm(s) ? s : ZE(s)
}

function _v(t) {
    return t.parent && Object.getPrototypeOf(t.parent) ? t.frameElement : null
}
function XE(t) {

        n = parseFloat(s.height) || 0;

        i = a ? t.offsetWidth : r,

        height: n,

    }
}
function Uj(t) {
    return Jn(t) ? t : t.contextElement
}
function nc(t) {

    }

function KL(t, s, r) {
    return s === void 0 && (s = !1), !r || s && r !== dn(t) ? !1 : s

function al(t, s, r, n) {
    s === void 0 && (s = !1),
    r === void 0 && (r = !1);
    const a = t.getBoundingClientRect(),
        i = Uj(t);
    let o = wa(1);
    s && (n ? Jn(n) && (o = nc(n)) : o = nc(t));
    const l = KL(i, r, n) ? JE(i) : wa(0);
    let c = (a.left + l.x) / o.x,
        d = (a.top + l.y) / o.y,
        u = a.width / o.x,
        m = a.height / o.y;

        const f = dn(i),
            y = n && Jn(n) ? dn(n) : n;

            x = _v(g);

                b = x.getBoundingClientRect(),
                p = ea(x),

                N = b.top + (x.clientTop + parseFloat(p.paddingTop)) * j.y;

            d *= j.y,
            u *= j.x,
            m *= j.y,

            d += N,

            x = _v(g)
        }
    }

        width: u,
        height: m,
        x: c,
        y: d
    })

function qj(t, s) {
    const r = Sp(t).scrollLeft;
    return s ? s.left + r : al(Ra(t)).left + r
}
function ek(t, s, r) {

    }

function YL(t) {
    let {elements: s, rect: r, offsetParent: n, strategy: a} = t;
    const i = a === "fixed",
        o = Ra(n),
        l = s ? Cp(s.floating) : !1;
    if (n === o || l && i)
        return r;
    let c = {
            scrollLeft: 0,
            scrollTop: 0
        },
        d = wa(1);

        m = Pa(n);
    if ((m || !m && !i) && ((td(n) !== "body" || cm(o)) && (c = Sp(n)), Pa(n))) {
        const y = al(n);
        d = nc(n),
        u.x = y.x + n.clientLeft,
        u.y = y.y + n.clientTop
    }
    const f = o && !m && !i ? ek(o, c, !0) : wa(0);
    return {
        width: r.width * d.x,
        height: r.height * d.y,
        x: r.x * d.x - c.scrollLeft * d.x + u.x + f.x,
        y: r.y * d.y - c.scrollTop * d.y + u.y + f.y
    }
}
function QL(t) {
    return Array.from(t.getClientRects())
}
function ZL(t) {

    }
}
function XL(t, s) {

    }

function JL(t, s) {

        n = r.top + t.clientTop,

        height: l,
        x: c,
        y: d
    }

function mw(t, s, r) {

function q3(t, s) {

        n = Math.abs(s.bottom - t.y),
        a = Math.abs(s.right - t.x),
        i = Math.abs(s.left - t.x);
    switch (Math.min(r, n, a, i)) {
    case i:
        return "left";
    case a:
        return "right";
    case r:
        return "top";
    case n:
        return "bottom";
    default:
        throw new Error("unreachable")
    }
}

function sz(t, s) {
    return s !== "rtl" ? t : t === "ArrowLeft" ? "ArrowRight" : t === "ArrowRight" ? "ArrowLeft" : t

    if (!(s === "vertical" && ["ArrowLeft", "ArrowRight"].includes(n)) && !(s === "horizontal" && ["ArrowUp", "ArrowDown"].includes(n)))
        return tz[n]
}

function eP(t) {
    return t ? "open" : "closed"
}
function Pf(t) {
    return t === "indeterminate"
}
function p0(t) {
    return Pf(t) ? "indeterminate" : t ? "checked" : "unchecked"

function Pz(t) {

    for (const r of t)
        if (r === s || (r.focus(), document.activeElement !== s))

}
function _z(t, s) {

}

}
function Az(t, s) {

            u = s[o].y;

    }

}

function C$(t, s, r, n, a) {

    }
    function d(g) {
        const x = t ? o(g) : l(g),
            j = s.map((p, v) => ({
                diff: u(p - x, 0),
                index: v
            })).sort((p, v) => as(p.diff) - as(v.diff)),
            {index: b} = j[0];
        return {
            index: b,
            distance: x
        }
    }
    function u(g, x) {
        const j = [g, g + r, g - r];
        if (!t)
            return g;
        if (!x)
            return c(j);
        const b = j.filter(p => N0(p) === x);
        return b.length ? c(b) : Yn(j) - r
    }

            b = u(j, x);

            index: g,
            distance: b
        }
    }

        const j = a.get() + g,
            {index: b, distance: p} = d(j),
            v = !t && i(j);

            return {
                index: b,
                distance: g
            };
        const N = s[b] - p,
            w = g + u(N, 0);
        return {
            index: b,
            distance: w
        }
    }
    return {
        byDistance: f,
        byIndex: m,
        shortcut: u
    }
}

function A$(t, s, r, n, a, i, o, l, c) {

    }

    }

    }

}
function R$() {
    let t = {},
        s;
    function r(d) {
        s = d
    }
    function n(d) {
        return t[d] || []
    }
    function a(d) {
        return n(d).forEach(u => u(s, d)), c
    }
    function i(d, u) {
        return t[d] = n(d).concat([u]), c
    }
    function o(d, u) {
        return t[d] = n(d).filter(m => m !== u), c
    }
    function l() {
        t = {}
    }
    const c = {
        init: r,
        emit: a,
        off: o,
        on: i,
        clear: l
    };
    return c
}

function D$(t) {
    function s(i, o) {
        return e_(i, o || {})
    }
    function r(i) {
        const o = i.breakpoints || {},
            l = Tu(o).filter(c => t.matchMedia(c).matches).map(c => o[c]).reduce((c, d) => s(c, d), {});
        return s(i, l)
    }
    function n(i) {
        return i.map(o => Tu(o.breakpoints || {})).reduce((o, l) => o.concat(l), []).map(t.matchMedia)
    }
    return {
        mergeOptions: s,
        optionsAtMedia: r,
        optionsMediaQueries: n
    }
}
function O$(t) {
    let s = [];
    function r(i, o) {
        return s = o.filter(({options: l}) => t.optionsAtMedia(l).active !== !1), s.forEach(l => l.init(i, t)), o.reduce((l, c) => Object.assign(l, {
            [c.name]: c
        }), {})
    }
    function n() {
        s = s.filter(i => i.destroy())
    }
    return {
        init: r,
        destroy: n
    }
}
function Af(t, s, r) {
    const n = t.ownerDocument,
        a = n.defaultView,
        i = D$(a),
        o = O$(i),
        l = Au(),
        c = R$(),
        {mergeOptions: d, optionsAtMedia: u, optionsMediaQueries: m} = i,
        {on: f, off: y, emit: g} = c,
        x = L;
    let j = !1,
        b,
        p = d(I$, Af.globalOptions),
        v = d(p),
        N = [],
        w,
        C,
        E;
    function k() {
        const {container: de, slides: le} = v;
        C = (Jv(de) ? t.querySelector(de) : de) || t.children[0];
        const ye = Jv(le) ? C.querySelectorAll(le) : le;
        E = [].slice.call(ye || C.children)
    }
    function D(de) {
        const le = M$(t, C, E, n, a, de, c);
        if (de.loop && !le.slideLooper.canLoop()) {
            const me = Object.assign({}, de, {
                loop: !1
            });
            return D(me)
        }
        return le
    }
    function K(de, le) {
        j || (p = d(p, de), v = u(p), N = le || N, k(), b = D(v), m([p, ...N.map(({options: me}) => me)]).forEach(me => l.add(me, "change", L)), v.active && (b.translate.to(b.location.get()), b.animation.init(), b.slidesInView.init(), b.slideFocus.init(re), b.eventHandler.init(re), b.resizeHandler.init(re), b.slidesHandler.init(re), b.options.loop && b.slideLooper.loop(), C.offsetParent && E.length && b.dragHandler.init(re), w = o.init(re, N)))
    }
    function L(de, le) {
        const me = O();
        R(),
        K(d({
            startIndex: me
        }, de), le),
        c.emit("reInit")
    }
    function R() {
        b.dragHandler.destroy(),
        b.eventStore.clear(),
        b.translate.clear(),
        b.slideLooper.clear(),
        b.resizeHandler.destroy(),
        b.slidesHandler.destroy(),
        b.slidesInView.destroy(),
        b.animation.destroy(),
        o.destroy(),
        l.clear()
    }
    function z() {
        j || (j = !0, l.clear(), R(), c.emit("destroy"), c.clear())
    }
    function H(de, le, me) {
        !v.active || j || (b.scrollBody.useBaseFriction().useDuration(le === !0 ? 0 : v.duration), b.scrollTo.index(de, me || 0))
    }
    function F(de) {
        const le = b.index.add(1).get();
        H(le, de, -1)
    }
    function A(de) {
        const le = b.index.add(-1).get();
        H(le, de, 1)
    }
    function P() {
        return b.index.add(1).get() !== O()
    }
    function I() {
        return b.index.add(-1).get() !== O()
    }
    function $() {
        return b.scrollSnapList
    }
    function ne() {
        return b.scrollProgress.get(b.offsetLocation.get())
    }
    function O() {
        return b.index.get()
    }
    function S() {
        return b.indexPrevious.get()
    }
    function B() {
        return b.slidesInView.get()
    }
    function ee() {
        return b.slidesInView.get(!1)
    }
    function ge() {
        return w
    }
    function Ne() {
        return b
    }
    function T() {
        return t
    }
    function te() {
        return C
    }
    function W() {
        return E
    }
    const re = {
        canScrollNext: P,
        canScrollPrev: I,
        containerNode: te,
        internalEngine: Ne,
        destroy: z,
        off: y,
        on: f,
        emit: g,
        plugins: ge,
        previousScrollSnap: S,
        reInit: x,
        rootNode: T,
        scrollNext: F,
        scrollPrev: A,
        scrollProgress: ne,
        scrollSnapList: $,
        scrollTo: H,
        selectedScrollSnap: O,
        slideNodes: W,
        slidesInView: B,
        slidesNotInView: ee
    };
    return K(s, r), setTimeout(() => c.emit("init"), 0), re
}

                throw new Error(n.message || "Error al eliminar importación del historial")
            }
            const r = await s.text();
            if (!r || r.trim() === "")
                return {
                    success: !0,
                    message: "Importación eliminada correctamente"
                };
            try {
                return JSON.parse(r)
            } catch (n) {
                return console.error("Error parsing JSON response:", n, "Response text:", r), {
                    success: !0,
                    message: "Importación eliminada correctamente"
                }
            }
        },
        async deleteAllImportHistory() {
            const t = await fetch("/api/import/clear-all", {
                method: "DELETE",
                headers: {
                    "Content-Type": "application/json"
                },
                credentials: "include"
            });
            if (!t.ok) {
                const r = await t.json().catch(() => ({
                    message: "Error desconocido"
                }));
                throw new Error(r.message || "Error al eliminar todo el historial de importaciones")
            }
            const s = await t.text();
            if (!s || s.trim() === "")
                return {
                    success: !0,
                    message: "Historial eliminado correctamente"
                };
            try {
                return JSON.parse(s)
            } catch (r) {
                return console.error("Error parsing JSON response:", r, "Response text:", s), {
                    success: !0,
                    message: "Historial eliminado correctamente"
                }
            }
        },
        async clearImportStatistics() {
            const t = await fetch("/api/import/history/stats", {
                method: "DELETE",
                headers: {
                    "Content-Type": "application/json"
                },
                credentials: "include"
            });
            if (!t.ok) {
                const r = await t.json().catch(() => ({
                    message: "Error desconocido"
                }));
                throw new Error(r.message || "Error al limpiar estadísticas de importación")
            }
            const s = await t.text();
            if (!s || s.trim() === "")
                return {
                    success: !0,
                    message: "Estadísticas limpiadas correctamente"
                };
            try {
                return JSON.parse(s)
            } catch (r) {
                return console.error("Error parsing JSON response:", r, "Response text:", s), {
                    success: !0,
                    message: "Estadísticas limpiadas correctamente"
                }
            }
        }
    },

function V_(t) {
    return t ? t.toLowerCase().trim().replace(/[áàäâã]/g, "a").replace(/[éèëê]/g, "e").replace(/[íìïî]/g, "i").replace(/[óòöôõ]/g, "o").replace(/[úùüû]/g, "u").replace(/[ñ]/g, "n").replace(/[ç]/g, "c").replace(/[^a-z0-9\s-]/g, "").replace(/\s+/g, "-").replace(/-+/g, "-").replace(/^-|-$/g, "") : ""
}
function oy(t) {
    return `/piezas/${V_(`${t.descripcionArticulo} ${t.vehicleMarca} ${t.vehicleModelo}`)}-${t.id}`
}
function Mu(t) {
    const s = t.anyo ? `-${t.anyo}` : "";
    return `/vehiculos/${V_(`${t.marca} ${t.modelo}${s}`)}-${t.id}`
}
function U_(t) {
    const s = t.match(/-(\d+)$/);
    return s ? parseInt(s[1]) : null
}

            },

        }),

var DV = t => {
    const {control: s, checked: r, bubbles: n=!0, defaultChecked: a, ...i} = t,
        o = h.useRef(null),
        l = Dp(r),
        c = Ep(s);

            m = window.HTMLInputElement.prototype,
            y = Object.getOwnPropertyDescriptor(m, "checked").set;

            const g = new Event("click", {
                bubbles: n
            });

            y.call(u, oo(r) ? !1 : r),
            u.dispatchEvent(g)
        }
    }, [l, r, n]);

        type: "checkbox",
        "aria-hidden": !0,
        defaultChecked: a ?? d.current,
        ...i,
        tabIndex: -1,
        ref: o,
        style: {
            ...t.style,
            ...c,
            position: "absolute",
            pointerEvents: "none",
            opacity: 0,
            margin: 0
        }
    })
};
function oo(t) {
    return t === "indeterminate"
}
function G_(t) {
    return oo(t) ? "indeterminate" : t ? "checked" : "unchecked"
}

function s1(t) {
    if (t.vehicles && t.vehicles.length > 0) {
        const s = t.vehicles[0];
        return {
            id: s.id,
            marca: s.marca,
            modelo: s.modelo,
            version: s.version || "",
            anyo: s.anyo,
            combustible: s.combustible,
            hasValidId: !!s.id
        }
    }
    return t.vehicleId || t.vehicleMarca || t.vehicleModelo ? {
        id: t.vehicleId,
        marca: t.vehicleMarca || "",
        modelo: t.vehicleModelo || "",
        version: t.vehicleVersion || "",
        anyo: t.vehicleAnyo,
        hasValidId: !!t.vehicleId
    } : t.idVehiculo && (t.vehicleMarca || t.vehicleModelo) ? {
        id: void 0,
        marca: t.vehicleMarca || "",
        modelo: t.vehicleModelo || "",
        version: t.vehicleVersion || "",
        anyo: t.vehicleAnyo,
        hasValidId: !1
    } : {
        id: void 0,
        marca: t.marcaVehiculo || "",
        modelo: t.modeloVehiculo || "",
        version: t.versionVehiculo || "",
        anyo: t.anyoVehiculo,
        hasValidId: !1
    }
}
function LV(t, s={}) {

        i = [t.marca, t.modelo, t.version].filter(Boolean);
    r && t.anyo && i.push(`(${t.anyo})`),
    a && t.id && i.push(`ID: ${t.id}`);
    let o = i.join(" ");
    return n ? o.toUpperCase() : o
}
function r1(t, s={}) {
    const {hideLinks: r=!1, contextVehicleId: n, includeYear: a=!1, uppercase: i=!1, showId: o=!1} = s,
        l = LV(t, {
            includeYear: a,
            uppercase: i
        }),
        c = !r && t.hasValidId && t.id !== n;
    return {
        vehicleText: l,
        shouldShowLink: c,
        vehicleId: t.id,
        linkTo: t.id ? `/vehiculos/${t.id}` : void 0,
        displayText: o && t.id ? `${l} (ID: ${t.id})` : l
    }
}

class hn extends Error {
    get errors()
    {
        return this.issues
    }
    constructor(s)
    {
        super(),
        this.issues = [],
        this.addIssue = n => {

        };

        Object.setPrototypeOf ? Object.setPrototypeOf(this, r) : this.__proto__ = r,

    }

            },

                        a(o.argumentsError);

                        }
                    }
            };

    }

    {

const zc = (t, s) => {
    let r;
    switch (t.code) {
    case Se.invalid_type:
        t.received === Le.undefined ? r = "Required" : r = `Expected ${t.expected}, received ${t.received}`;
        break;
    case Se.invalid_literal:
        r = `Invalid literal value, expected ${JSON.stringify(t.expected, kt.jsonStringifyReplacer)}`;
        break;
    case Se.unrecognized_keys:
        r = `Unrecognized key(s) in object: ${kt.joinValues(t.keys, ", ")}`;
        break;
    case Se.invalid_union:
        r = "Invalid input";
        break;
    case Se.invalid_union_discriminator:
        r = `Invalid discriminator value. Expected ${kt.joinValues(t.options)}`;
        break;
    case Se.invalid_enum_value:
        r = `Invalid enum value. Expected ${kt.joinValues(t.options)}, received '${t.received}'`;
        break;
    case Se.invalid_arguments:
        r = "Invalid function arguments";
        break;
    case Se.invalid_return_type:
        r = "Invalid function return type";
        break;
    case Se.invalid_date:
        r = "Invalid date";
        break;
    case Se.invalid_string:
        typeof t.validation == "object" ? "includes" in t.validation ? (r = `Invalid input: must include "${t.validation.includes}"`, typeof t.validation.position == "number" && (r = `${r} at one or more positions greater than or equal to ${t.validation.position}`)) : "startsWith" in t.validation ? r = `Invalid input: must start with "${t.validation.startsWith}"` : "endsWith" in t.validation ? r = `Invalid input: must end with "${t.validation.endsWith}"` : kt.assertNever(t.validation) : t.validation !== "regex" ? r = `Invalid ${t.validation}` : r = "Invalid";
        break;
    case Se.too_small:
        t.type === "array" ? r = `Array must contain ${t.exact ? "exactly" : t.inclusive ? "at least" : "more than"} ${t.minimum} element(s)` : t.type === "string" ? r = `String must contain ${t.exact ? "exactly" : t.inclusive ? "at least" : "over"} ${t.minimum} character(s)` : t.type === "number" ? r = `Number must be ${t.exact ? "exactly equal to " : t.inclusive ? "greater than or equal to " : "greater than "}${t.minimum}` : t.type === "date" ? r = `Date must be ${t.exact ? "exactly equal to " : t.inclusive ? "greater than or equal to " : "greater than "}${new Date(Number(t.minimum))}` : r = "Invalid input";
        break;
    case Se.too_big:
        t.type === "array" ? r = `Array must contain ${t.exact ? "exactly" : t.inclusive ? "at most" : "less than"} ${t.maximum} element(s)` : t.type === "string" ? r = `String must contain ${t.exact ? "exactly" : t.inclusive ? "at most" : "under"} ${t.maximum} character(s)` : t.type === "number" ? r = `Number must be ${t.exact ? "exactly" : t.inclusive ? "less than or equal to" : "less than"} ${t.maximum}` : t.type === "bigint" ? r = `BigInt must be ${t.exact ? "exactly" : t.inclusive ? "less than or equal to" : "less than"} ${t.maximum}` : t.type === "date" ? r = `Date must be ${t.exact ? "exactly" : t.inclusive ? "smaller than or equal to" : "smaller than"} ${new Date(Number(t.maximum))}` : r = "Invalid input";
        break;
    case Se.custom:
        r = "Invalid input";
        break;
    case Se.invalid_intersection_types:
        r = "Intersection results could not be merged";
        break;
    case Se.not_multiple_of:
        r = `Number must be a multiple of ${t.multipleOf}`;
        break;
    case Se.not_finite:
        r = "Number must be finite";
        break;
    default:
        r = s.defaultError,
        kt.assertNever(t)
    }
    return {
        message: r
    }
};

class mr {

    static mergeArray(s, r)

                        position: i.position
                    },
                    message: i.message
                }), n.dirty()) : i.kind === "toLowerCase" ? s.data = s.data.toLowerCase() : i.kind === "toUpperCase" ? s.data = s.data.toUpperCase() : i.kind === "startsWith" ? s.data.startsWith(i.value) || (a = this._getOrReturnCtx(s, a), Re(a, {

                        startsWith: i.value
                    },
                    message: i.message
                }), n.dirty()) : i.kind === "endsWith" ? s.data.endsWith(i.value) || (a = this._getOrReturnCtx(s, a), Re(a, {

                    },

                    validation: "datetime",
                    message: i.message
                }), n.dirty()) : i.kind === "date" ? q9.test(s.data) || (a = this._getOrReturnCtx(s, a), Re(a, {
                    code: Se.invalid_string,

                    message: i.message
                }), n.dirty()) : i.kind === "time" ? B9(i).test(s.data) || (a = this._getOrReturnCtx(s, a), Re(a, {
                    code: Se.invalid_string,
                    validation: "time",
                    message: i.message
                }), n.dirty()) : i.kind === "duration" ? I9.test(s.data) || (a = this._getOrReturnCtx(s, a), Re(a, {
                    validation: "duration",
                    code: Se.invalid_string,
                    message: i.message
                }), n.dirty()) : i.kind === "ip" ? H9(s.data, i.version) || (a = this._getOrReturnCtx(s, a), Re(a, {

            status: n.value,
            value: s.data
        }
    }

function K9(t, s) {
    const r = (t.toString().split(".")[1] || "").length,
        n = (s.toString().split(".")[1] || "").length,
        a = r > n ? r : n,
        i = parseInt(t.toFixed(a).replace(".", "")),
        o = parseInt(s.toFixed(a).replace(".", ""));
    return i % o / Math.pow(10, a)
}
class xo extends jt {
    constructor()
    {
        super(...arguments),
        this.min = this.gte,
        this.max = this.lte,
        this.step = this.multipleOf
    }
    _parse(s)
    {
        if (this._def.coerce && (s.data = Number(s.data)), this._getType(s) !== Le.number) {
            const i = this._getOrReturnCtx(s);
            return Re(i, {
                code: Se.invalid_type,
                expected: Le.number,
                received: i.parsedType
            }), it
        }
        let n;
        const a = new mr;
        for (const i of this._def.checks)
            i.kind === "int" ? kt.isInteger(s.data) || (n = this._getOrReturnCtx(s, n), Re(n, {
                code: Se.invalid_type,
                expected: "integer",
                received: "float",
                message: i.message
            }), a.dirty()) : i.kind === "min" ? (i.inclusive ? s.data < i.value : s.data <= i.value) && (n = this._getOrReturnCtx(s, n), Re(n, {
                code: Se.too_small,
                minimum: i.value,
                type: "number",
                inclusive: i.inclusive,
                exact: !1,
                message: i.message
            }), a.dirty()) : i.kind === "max" ? (i.inclusive ? s.data > i.value : s.data >= i.value) && (n = this._getOrReturnCtx(s, n), Re(n, {
                code: Se.too_big,
                maximum: i.value,
                type: "number",
                inclusive: i.inclusive,
                exact: !1,
                message: i.message
            }), a.dirty()) : i.kind === "multipleOf" ? K9(s.data, i.value) !== 0 && (n = this._getOrReturnCtx(s, n), Re(n, {
                code: Se.not_multiple_of,
                multipleOf: i.value,
                message: i.message
            }), a.dirty()) : i.kind === "finite" ? Number.isFinite(s.data) || (n = this._getOrReturnCtx(s, n), Re(n, {
                code: Se.not_finite,
                message: i.message
            }), a.dirty()) : kt.assertNever(i);
        return {
            status: a.value,
            value: s.data
        }
    }
    gte(s, r)
    {
        return this.setLimit("min", s, !0, Ke.toString(r))
    }
    gt(s, r)
    {
        return this.setLimit("min", s, !1, Ke.toString(r))
    }
    lte(s, r)
    {
        return this.setLimit("max", s, !0, Ke.toString(r))
    }
    lt(s, r)
    {
        return this.setLimit("max", s, !1, Ke.toString(r))
    }
    setLimit(s, r, n, a)
    {
        return new xo({
            ...this._def,
            checks: [...this._def.checks, {
                kind: s,
                value: r,
                inclusive: n,
                message: Ke.toString(a)
            }]
        })
    }
    _addCheck(s)
    {
        return new xo({
            ...this._def,
            checks: [...this._def.checks, s]
        })
    }
    int(s)
    {
        return this._addCheck({
            kind: "int",
            message: Ke.toString(s)
        })
    }
    positive(s)
    {
        return this._addCheck({
            kind: "min",
            value: 0,
            inclusive: !1,
            message: Ke.toString(s)
        })
    }
    negative(s)
    {
        return this._addCheck({
            kind: "max",
            value: 0,
            inclusive: !1,
            message: Ke.toString(s)
        })
    }
    nonpositive(s)
    {
        return this._addCheck({
            kind: "max",
            value: 0,
            inclusive: !0,
            message: Ke.toString(s)
        })
    }
    nonnegative(s)
    {
        return this._addCheck({
            kind: "min",
            value: 0,
            inclusive: !0,
            message: Ke.toString(s)
        })
    }
    multipleOf(s, r)
    {
        return this._addCheck({
            kind: "multipleOf",
            value: s,
            message: Ke.toString(r)
        })
    }
    finite(s)
    {
        return this._addCheck({
            kind: "finite",
            message: Ke.toString(s)
        })
    }
    safe(s)
    {
        return this._addCheck({
            kind: "min",
            inclusive: !0,
            value: Number.MIN_SAFE_INTEGER,
            message: Ke.toString(s)
        })._addCheck({
            kind: "max",
            inclusive: !0,
            value: Number.MAX_SAFE_INTEGER,
            message: Ke.toString(s)
        })
    }
    get minValue()
    {
        let s = null;
        for (const r of this._def.checks)
            r.kind === "min" && (s === null || r.value > s) && (s = r.value);
        return s
    }
    get maxValue()
    {
        let s = null;
        for (const r of this._def.checks)
            r.kind === "max" && (s === null || r.value < s) && (s = r.value);
        return s
    }
    get isInt()
    {
        return !!this._def.checks.find(s => s.kind === "int" || s.kind === "multipleOf" && kt.isInteger(s.value))
    }
    get isFinite()
    {
        let s = null,
            r = null;
        for (const n of this._def.checks) {
            if (n.kind === "finite" || n.kind === "int" || n.kind === "multipleOf")
                return !0;
            n.kind === "min" ? (r === null || n.value > r) && (r = n.value) : n.kind === "max" && (s === null || n.value < s) && (s = n.value)
        }
        return Number.isFinite(r) && Number.isFinite(s)
    }
}

    typeName: nt.ZodNumber,

    ...pt(t)

class go extends jt {
    constructor()
    {
        super(...arguments),
        this.min = this.gte,
        this.max = this.lte
    }
    _parse(s)
    {
        if (this._def.coerce)
            try {
                s.data = BigInt(s.data)
            } catch {
                return this._getInvalidInput(s)
            }
        if (this._getType(s) !== Le.bigint)
            return this._getInvalidInput(s);
        let n;
        const a = new mr;
        for (const i of this._def.checks)
            i.kind === "min" ? (i.inclusive ? s.data < i.value : s.data <= i.value) && (n = this._getOrReturnCtx(s, n), Re(n, {
                code: Se.too_small,
                type: "bigint",
                minimum: i.value,
                inclusive: i.inclusive,
                message: i.message
            }), a.dirty()) : i.kind === "max" ? (i.inclusive ? s.data > i.value : s.data >= i.value) && (n = this._getOrReturnCtx(s, n), Re(n, {
                code: Se.too_big,
                type: "bigint",
                maximum: i.value,
                inclusive: i.inclusive,
                message: i.message
            }), a.dirty()) : i.kind === "multipleOf" ? s.data % i.value !== BigInt(0) && (n = this._getOrReturnCtx(s, n), Re(n, {
                code: Se.not_multiple_of,
                multipleOf: i.value,
                message: i.message
            }), a.dirty()) : kt.assertNever(i);
        return {
            status: a.value,
            value: s.data
        }
    }
    _getInvalidInput(s)
    {
        const r = this._getOrReturnCtx(s);
        return Re(r, {
            code: Se.invalid_type,
            expected: Le.bigint,
            received: r.parsedType
        }), it
    }
    gte(s, r)
    {
        return this.setLimit("min", s, !0, Ke.toString(r))
    }
    gt(s, r)
    {
        return this.setLimit("min", s, !1, Ke.toString(r))
    }
    lte(s, r)
    {
        return this.setLimit("max", s, !0, Ke.toString(r))
    }
    lt(s, r)
    {
        return this.setLimit("max", s, !1, Ke.toString(r))
    }
    setLimit(s, r, n, a)
    {
        return new go({
            ...this._def,
            checks: [...this._def.checks, {
                kind: s,
                value: r,
                inclusive: n,
                message: Ke.toString(a)
            }]
        })
    }
    _addCheck(s)
    {
        return new go({
            ...this._def,
            checks: [...this._def.checks, s]
        })
    }
    positive(s)
    {
        return this._addCheck({
            kind: "min",
            value: BigInt(0),
            inclusive: !1,
            message: Ke.toString(s)
        })
    }
    negative(s)
    {
        return this._addCheck({
            kind: "max",
            value: BigInt(0),
            inclusive: !1,
            message: Ke.toString(s)
        })
    }
    nonpositive(s)
    {
        return this._addCheck({
            kind: "max",
            value: BigInt(0),
            inclusive: !0,
            message: Ke.toString(s)
        })
    }
    nonnegative(s)
    {
        return this._addCheck({
            kind: "min",
            value: BigInt(0),
            inclusive: !0,
            message: Ke.toString(s)
        })
    }
    multipleOf(s, r)
    {
        return this._addCheck({
            kind: "multipleOf",
            value: s,
            message: Ke.toString(r)
        })
    }
    get minValue()
    {
        let s = null;
        for (const r of this._def.checks)
            r.kind === "min" && (s === null || r.value > s) && (s = r.value);
        return s
    }
    get maxValue()
    {
        let s = null;
        for (const r of this._def.checks)
            r.kind === "max" && (s === null || r.value < s) && (s = r.value);
        return s
    }
}

class Lu extends jt {
    _parse(s)
    {
        if (this._def.coerce && (s.data = !!s.data), this._getType(s) !== Le.boolean) {
            const n = this._getOrReturnCtx(s);
            return Re(n, {
                code: Se.invalid_type,
                expected: Le.boolean,
                received: n.parsedType
            }), it
        }
        return kr(s.data)
    }
}

class hl extends jt {
    _parse(s)
    {
        if (this._def.coerce && (s.data = new Date(s.data)), this._getType(s) !== Le.date) {
            const i = this._getOrReturnCtx(s);
            return Re(i, {
                code: Se.invalid_type,
                expected: Le.date,
                received: i.parsedType
            }), it
        }
        if (isNaN(s.data.getTime())) {
            const i = this._getOrReturnCtx(s);
            return Re(i, {
                code: Se.invalid_date
            }), it
        }
        const n = new mr;
        let a;
        for (const i of this._def.checks)
            i.kind === "min" ? s.data.getTime() < i.value && (a = this._getOrReturnCtx(s, a), Re(a, {
                code: Se.too_small,
                message: i.message,
                inclusive: !0,
                exact: !1,
                minimum: i.value,
                type: "date"
            }), n.dirty()) : i.kind === "max" ? s.data.getTime() > i.value && (a = this._getOrReturnCtx(s, a), Re(a, {
                code: Se.too_big,
                message: i.message,
                inclusive: !0,
                exact: !1,
                maximum: i.value,
                type: "date"
            }), n.dirty()) : kt.assertNever(i);
        return {
            status: n.value,
            value: new Date(s.data.getTime())
        }
    }
    _addCheck(s)
    {
        return new hl({
            ...this._def,
            checks: [...this._def.checks, s]
        })
    }
    min(s, r)
    {
        return this._addCheck({
            kind: "min",
            value: s.getTime(),
            message: Ke.toString(r)
        })
    }
    max(s, r)
    {
        return this._addCheck({
            kind: "max",
            value: s.getTime(),
            message: Ke.toString(r)
        })
    }
    get minDate()
    {
        let s = null;
        for (const r of this._def.checks)
            r.kind === "min" && (s === null || r.value > s) && (s = r.value);
        return s != null ? new Date(s) : null
    }
    get maxDate()
    {
        let s = null;
        for (const r of this._def.checks)
            r.kind === "max" && (s === null || r.value < s) && (s = r.value);
        return s != null ? new Date(s) : null
    }
}
hl.create = t => new hl({
    checks: [],
    coerce: (t == null ? void 0 : t.coerce) || !1,
    typeName: nt.ZodDate,
    ...pt(t)
});
class Vf extends jt {

    {
        if (this._getType(s) !== Le.symbol) {
            const n = this._getOrReturnCtx(s);
            return Re(n, {
                code: Se.invalid_type,
                expected: Le.symbol,
                received: n.parsedType
            }), it
        }
        return kr(s.data)
    }
}

class Qn extends jt {
    _parse(s)
    {
        const {ctx: r, status: n} = this._processInputParams(s),
            a = this._def;
        if (r.parsedType !== Le.array)
            return Re(r, {
                code: Se.invalid_type,
                expected: Le.array,
                received: r.parsedType
            }), it;
        if (a.exactLength !== null) {
            const o = r.data.length > a.exactLength.value,
                l = r.data.length < a.exactLength.value;
            (o || l) && (Re(r, {
                code: o ? Se.too_big : Se.too_small,
                minimum: l ? a.exactLength.value : void 0,
                maximum: o ? a.exactLength.value : void 0,
                type: "array",
                inclusive: !0,
                exact: !0,
                message: a.exactLength.message
            }), n.dirty())
        }
        if (a.minLength !== null && r.data.length < a.minLength.value && (Re(r, {
            code: Se.too_small,
            minimum: a.minLength.value,
            type: "array",
            inclusive: !0,
            exact: !1,
            message: a.minLength.message
        }), n.dirty()), a.maxLength !== null && r.data.length > a.maxLength.value && (Re(r, {
            code: Se.too_big,
            maximum: a.maxLength.value,
            type: "array",
            inclusive: !0,
            exact: !1,
            message: a.maxLength.message
        }), n.dirty()), r.common.async)
            return Promise.all([...r.data].map((o, l) => a.type._parseAsync(new Ta(r, o, r.path, l)))).then(o => mr.mergeArray(n, o));
        const i = [...r.data].map((o, l) => a.type._parseSync(new Ta(r, o, r.path, l)));
        return mr.mergeArray(n, i)
    }
    get element()
    {
        return this._def.type
    }
    min(s, r)
    {
        return new Qn({
            ...this._def,
            minLength: {
                value: s,
                message: Ke.toString(r)
            }
        })
    }
    max(s, r)
    {
        return new Qn({
            ...this._def,
            maxLength: {
                value: s,
                message: Ke.toString(r)
            }
        })
    }
    length(s, r)
    {
        return new Qn({
            ...this._def,
            exactLength: {
                value: s,
                message: Ke.toString(r)
            }
        })
    }
    nonempty(s)
    {
        return this.min(1, s)
    }
}
Qn.create = (t, s) => new Qn({
    type: t,
    minLength: null,
    maxLength: null,
    exactLength: null,
    typeName: nt.ZodArray,
    ...pt(s)
});
function Dl(t) {
    if (t instanceof rs) {
        const s = {};
        for (const r in t.shape) {
            const n = t.shape[r];
            s[r] = Sa.create(Dl(n))
        }
        return new rs({
            ...t._def,
            shape: () => s
        })
    } else
        return t instanceof Qn ? new Qn({
            ...t._def,
            type: Dl(t.element)
        }) : t instanceof Sa ? Sa.create(Dl(t.unwrap())) : t instanceof yo ? yo.create(Dl(t.unwrap())) : t instanceof Aa ? Aa.create(t.items.map(s => Dl(s))) : t
}
class rs extends jt {
    constructor()
    {
        super(...arguments),
        this._cached = null,
        this.nonstrict = this.passthrough,
        this.augment = this.extend
    }
    _getCached()
    {
        if (this._cached !== null)
            return this._cached;
        const s = this._def.shape(),
            r = kt.objectKeys(s);
        return this._cached = {
            shape: s,
            keys: r
        }
    }
    _parse(s)
    {
        if (this._getType(s) !== Le.object) {
            const d = this._getOrReturnCtx(s);
            return Re(d, {
                code: Se.invalid_type,
                expected: Le.object,
                received: d.parsedType
            }), it
        }
        const {status: n, ctx: a} = this._processInputParams(s),
            {shape: i, keys: o} = this._getCached(),
            l = [];
        if (!(this._def.catchall instanceof bi && this._def.unknownKeys === "strip"))
            for (const d in a.data)
                o.includes(d) || l.push(d);
        const c = [];
        for (const d of o) {
            const u = i[d],
                m = a.data[d];
            c.push({
                key: {
                    status: "valid",
                    value: d
                },
                value: u._parse(new Ta(a, m, a.path, d)),
                alwaysSet: d in a.data
            })
        }
        if (this._def.catchall instanceof bi) {
            const d = this._def.unknownKeys;
            if (d === "passthrough")
                for (const u of l)
                    c.push({
                        key: {
                            status: "valid",
                            value: u
                        },
                        value: {
                            status: "valid",
                            value: a.data[u]
                        }
                    });
            else if (d === "strict")
                l.length > 0 && (Re(a, {
                    code: Se.unrecognized_keys,
                    keys: l
                }), n.dirty());
            else if (d !== "strip")
                throw new Error("Internal ZodObject error: invalid unknownKeys value.")
        } else {
            const d = this._def.catchall;
            for (const u of l) {
                const m = a.data[u];
                c.push({
                    key: {
                        status: "valid",
                        value: u
                    },
                    value: d._parse(new Ta(a, m, a.path, u)),
                    alwaysSet: u in a.data
                })
            }
        }
        return a.common.async ? Promise.resolve().then(async () => {
            const d = [];
            for (const u of c) {
                const m = await u.key,
                    f = await u.value;
                d.push({
                    key: m,
                    value: f,
                    alwaysSet: u.alwaysSet
                })
            }
            return d
        }).then(d => mr.mergeObjectSync(n, d)) : mr.mergeObjectSync(n, c)
    }
    get shape()
    {
        return this._def.shape()
    }
    strict(s)
    {
        return Ke.errToObj, new rs({
            ...this._def,
            unknownKeys: "strict",
            ...s !== void 0 ? {
                errorMap: (r, n) => {
                    var a,
                        i,
                        o,
                        l;
                    const c = (o = (i = (a = this._def).errorMap) === null || i === void 0 ? void 0 : i.call(a, r, n).message) !== null && o !== void 0 ? o : n.defaultError;
                    return r.code === "unrecognized_keys" ? {
                        message: (l = Ke.errToObj(s).message) !== null && l !== void 0 ? l : c
                    } : {
                        message: c
                    }
                }
            } : {}
        })
    }
    strip()
    {
        return new rs({
            ...this._def,
            unknownKeys: "strip"
        })
    }
    passthrough()
    {
        return new rs({
            ...this._def,
            unknownKeys: "passthrough"
        })
    }
    extend(s)
    {
        return new rs({
            ...this._def,
            shape: () => ({
                ...this._def.shape(),
                ...s
            })
        })
    }
    merge(s)
    {
        return new rs({
            unknownKeys: s._def.unknownKeys,
            catchall: s._def.catchall,
            shape: () => ({
                ...this._def.shape(),
                ...s._def.shape()
            }),
            typeName: nt.ZodObject
        })
    }
    setKey(s, r)
    {
        return this.augment({
            [s]: r
        })
    }
    catchall(s)
    {
        return new rs({
            ...this._def,
            catchall: s
        })
    }
    pick(s)
    {
        const r = {};
        return kt.objectKeys(s).forEach(n => {
            s[n] && this.shape[n] && (r[n] = this.shape[n])
        }), new rs({
            ...this._def,
            shape: () => r
        })
    }
    omit(s)
    {
        const r = {};
        return kt.objectKeys(this.shape).forEach(n => {
            s[n] || (r[n] = this.shape[n])
        }), new rs({
            ...this._def,
            shape: () => r
        })
    }
    deepPartial()
    {
        return Dl(this)
    }
    partial(s)
    {
        const r = {};
        return kt.objectKeys(this.shape).forEach(n => {
            const a = this.shape[n];
            s && !s[n] ? r[n] = a : r[n] = a.optional()
        }), new rs({
            ...this._def,
            shape: () => r
        })
    }
    required(s)
    {
        const r = {};
        return kt.objectKeys(this.shape).forEach(n => {
            if (s && !s[n])
                r[n] = this.shape[n];
            else {
                let i = this.shape[n];
                for (; i instanceof Sa;)
                    i = i._def.innerType;
                r[n] = i
            }
        }), new rs({
            ...this._def,
            shape: () => r
        })
    }
    keyof()
    {
        return RT(kt.objectKeys(this.shape))
    }
}
rs.create = (t, s) => new rs({
    shape: () => t,
    unknownKeys: "strip",
    catchall: bi.create(),
    typeName: nt.ZodObject,
    ...pt(s)
});
rs.strictCreate = (t, s) => new rs({
    shape: () => t,
    unknownKeys: "strict",
    catchall: bi.create(),
    typeName: nt.ZodObject,
    ...pt(s)
});
rs.lazycreate = (t, s) => new rs({
    shape: t,
    unknownKeys: "strip",
    catchall: bi.create(),
    typeName: nt.ZodObject,
    ...pt(s)
});
class $u extends jt {
    _parse(s)
    {
        const {ctx: r} = this._processInputParams(s),
            n = this._def.options;
        function a(i) {
            for (const l of i)
                if (l.result.status === "valid")
                    return l.result;
            for (const l of i)
                if (l.result.status === "dirty")
                    return r.common.issues.push(...l.ctx.common.issues), l.result;
            const o = i.map(l => new hn(l.ctx.common.issues));
            return Re(r, {
                code: Se.invalid_union,
                unionErrors: o
            }), it
        }
        if (r.common.async)
            return Promise.all(n.map(async i => {
                const o = {
                    ...r,
                    common: {
                        ...r.common,
                        issues: []
                    },
                    parent: null
                };
                return {
                    result: await i._parseAsync({
                        data: r.data,
                        path: r.path,
                        parent: o
                    }),
                    ctx: o
                }
            })).then(a);
        {
            let i;
            const o = [];
            for (const c of n) {
                const d = {
                        ...r,
                        common: {
                            ...r.common,
                            issues: []
                        },
                        parent: null
                    },
                    u = c._parseSync({
                        data: r.data,
                        path: r.path,
                        parent: d
                    });
                if (u.status === "valid")
                    return u;
                u.status === "dirty" && !i && (i = {
                    result: u,
                    ctx: d
                }),
                d.common.issues.length && o.push(d.common.issues)
            }
            if (i)
                return r.common.issues.push(...i.ctx.common.issues), i.result;
            const l = o.map(c => new hn(c));
            return Re(r, {
                code: Se.invalid_union,
                unionErrors: l
            }), it
        }
    }
    get options()
    {
        return this._def.options
    }
}
$u.create = (t, s) => new $u({
    options: t,
    typeName: nt.ZodUnion,
    ...pt(s)
});
const Ba = t => t instanceof qu ? Ba(t.schema) : t instanceof ta ? Ba(t.innerType()) : t instanceof Bu ? [t.value] : t instanceof vo ? t.options : t instanceof Hu ? kt.objectValues(t.enum) : t instanceof Wu ? Ba(t._def.innerType) : t instanceof Fu ? [void 0] : t instanceof zu ? [null] : t instanceof Sa ? [void 0, ...Ba(t.unwrap())] : t instanceof yo ? [null, ...Ba(t.unwrap())] : t instanceof U0 || t instanceof Ku ? Ba(t.unwrap()) : t instanceof Gu ? Ba(t._def.innerType) : [];
class Xp extends jt {
    _parse(s)
    {
        const {ctx: r} = this._processInputParams(s);
        if (r.parsedType !== Le.object)
            return Re(r, {
                code: Se.invalid_type,
                expected: Le.object,
                received: r.parsedType
            }), it;
        const n = this.discriminator,
            a = r.data[n],
            i = this.optionsMap.get(a);
        return i ? r.common.async ? i._parseAsync({
            data: r.data,
            path: r.path,
            parent: r
        }) : i._parseSync({
            data: r.data,
            path: r.path,
            parent: r
        }) : (Re(r, {
            code: Se.invalid_union_discriminator,
            options: Array.from(this.optionsMap.keys()),
            path: [n]
        }), it)
    }
    get discriminator()
    {
        return this._def.discriminator
    }
    get options()
    {
        return this._def.options
    }
    get optionsMap()
    {
        return this._def.optionsMap
    }
    static create(s, r, n)
    {
        const a = new Map;
        for (const i of r) {
            const o = Ba(i.shape[s]);
            if (!o.length)
                throw new Error(`A discriminator value for key \`${s}\` could not be extracted from all schema options`);
            for (const l of o) {
                if (a.has(l))
                    throw new Error(`Discriminator property ${String(s)} has duplicate value ${String(l)}`);
                a.set(l, i)
            }
        }
        return new Xp({
            typeName: nt.ZodDiscriminatedUnion,
            discriminator: s,
            options: r,
            optionsMap: a,
            ...pt(n)
        })
    }
}
function hy(t, s) {
    const r = Ka(t),
        n = Ka(s);
    if (t === s)
        return {
            valid: !0,
            data: t
        };
    if (r === Le.object && n === Le.object) {
        const a = kt.objectKeys(s),
            i = kt.objectKeys(t).filter(l => a.indexOf(l) !== -1),
            o = {
                ...t,
                ...s
            };
        for (const l of i) {
            const c = hy(t[l], s[l]);
            if (!c.valid)
                return {
                    valid: !1
                };
            o[l] = c.data
        }
        return {
            valid: !0,
            data: o
        }
    } else if (r === Le.array && n === Le.array) {
        if (t.length !== s.length)
            return {
                valid: !1
            };
        const a = [];
        for (let i = 0; i < t.length; i++) {
            const o = t[i],
                l = s[i],
                c = hy(o, l);
            if (!c.valid)
                return {
                    valid: !1
                };
            a.push(c.data)
        }
        return {
            valid: !0,
            data: a
        }
    } else
        return r === Le.date && n === Le.date && +t == +s ? {
            valid: !0,
            data: t
        } : {
            valid: !1
        }
}
class Vu extends jt {
    _parse(s)
    {
        const {status: r, ctx: n} = this._processInputParams(s),
            a = (i, o) => {
                if (uy(i) || uy(o))
                    return it;
                const l = hy(i.value, o.value);
                return l.valid ? ((my(i) || my(o)) && r.dirty(), {
                    status: r.value,
                    value: l.data
                }) : (Re(n, {
                    code: Se.invalid_intersection_types
                }), it)
            };
        return n.common.async ? Promise.all([this._def.left._parseAsync({
            data: n.data,
            path: n.path,
            parent: n
        }), this._def.right._parseAsync({
            data: n.data,
            path: n.path,
            parent: n
        })]).then(([i, o]) => a(i, o)) : a(this._def.left._parseSync({
            data: n.data,
            path: n.path,
            parent: n
        }), this._def.right._parseSync({
            data: n.data,
            path: n.path,
            parent: n
        }))
    }
}
Vu.create = (t, s, r) => new Vu({
    left: t,
    right: s,
    typeName: nt.ZodIntersection,
    ...pt(r)
});
class Aa extends jt {
    _parse(s)
    {
        const {status: r, ctx: n} = this._processInputParams(s);
        if (n.parsedType !== Le.array)
            return Re(n, {
                code: Se.invalid_type,
                expected: Le.array,
                received: n.parsedType
            }), it;
        if (n.data.length < this._def.items.length)
            return Re(n, {
                code: Se.too_small,
                minimum: this._def.items.length,
                inclusive: !0,
                exact: !1,
                type: "array"
            }), it;
        !this._def.rest && n.data.length > this._def.items.length && (Re(n, {
            code: Se.too_big,
            maximum: this._def.items.length,
            inclusive: !0,
            exact: !1,
            type: "array"
        }), r.dirty());
        const i = [...n.data].map((o, l) => {
            const c = this._def.items[l] || this._def.rest;
            return c ? c._parse(new Ta(n, o, n.path, l)) : null
        }).filter(o => !!o);
        return n.common.async ? Promise.all(i).then(o => mr.mergeArray(r, o)) : mr.mergeArray(r, i)
    }
    get items()
    {
        return this._def.items
    }
    rest(s)
    {
        return new Aa({
            ...this._def,
            rest: s
        })
    }
}
Aa.create = (t, s) => {
    if (!Array.isArray(t))
        throw new Error("You must pass an array of schemas to z.tuple([ ... ])");
    return new Aa({
        items: t,
        typeName: nt.ZodTuple,
        rest: null,
        ...pt(s)
    })
};
class Uu extends jt {
    get keySchema()
    {
        return this._def.keyType
    }
    get valueSchema()
    {
        return this._def.valueType
    }
    _parse(s)
    {
        const {status: r, ctx: n} = this._processInputParams(s);
        if (n.parsedType !== Le.object)
            return Re(n, {
                code: Se.invalid_type,
                expected: Le.object,
                received: n.parsedType
            }), it;
        const a = [],
            i = this._def.keyType,
            o = this._def.valueType;
        for (const l in n.data)
            a.push({
                key: i._parse(new Ta(n, l, n.path, l)),
                value: o._parse(new Ta(n, n.data[l], n.path, l)),
                alwaysSet: l in n.data
            });
        return n.common.async ? mr.mergeObjectAsync(r, a) : mr.mergeObjectSync(r, a)
    }
    get element()
    {
        return this._def.valueType
    }
    static create(s, r, n)
    {
        return r instanceof jt ? new Uu({
            keyType: s,
            valueType: r,
            typeName: nt.ZodRecord,
            ...pt(n)
        }) : new Uu({
            keyType: Bn.create(),
            valueType: s,
            typeName: nt.ZodRecord,
            ...pt(r)
        })
    }
}
class qf extends jt {
    get keySchema()
    {
        return this._def.keyType
    }
    get valueSchema()
    {
        return this._def.valueType
    }
    _parse(s)
    {
        const {status: r, ctx: n} = this._processInputParams(s);
        if (n.parsedType !== Le.map)
            return Re(n, {
                code: Se.invalid_type,
                expected: Le.map,
                received: n.parsedType
            }), it;
        const a = this._def.keyType,
            i = this._def.valueType,
            o = [...n.data.entries()].map(([l, c], d) => ({
                key: a._parse(new Ta(n, l, n.path, [d, "key"])),
                value: i._parse(new Ta(n, c, n.path, [d, "value"]))
            }));
        if (n.common.async) {
            const l = new Map;
            return Promise.resolve().then(async () => {
                for (const c of o) {
                    const d = await c.key,
                        u = await c.value;
                    if (d.status === "aborted" || u.status === "aborted")
                        return it;
                    (d.status === "dirty" || u.status === "dirty") && r.dirty(),
                    l.set(d.value, u.value)
                }
                return {
                    status: r.value,
                    value: l
                }
            })
        } else {
            const l = new Map;
            for (const c of o) {
                const d = c.key,
                    u = c.value;
                if (d.status === "aborted" || u.status === "aborted")
                    return it;
                (d.status === "dirty" || u.status === "dirty") && r.dirty(),
                l.set(d.value, u.value)
            }
            return {
                status: r.value,
                value: l
            }
        }
    }
}

class fl extends jt {
    _parse(s)
    {
        const {status: r, ctx: n} = this._processInputParams(s);
        if (n.parsedType !== Le.set)
            return Re(n, {
                code: Se.invalid_type,
                expected: Le.set,
                received: n.parsedType
            }), it;
        const a = this._def;
        a.minSize !== null && n.data.size < a.minSize.value && (Re(n, {
            code: Se.too_small,
            minimum: a.minSize.value,
            type: "set",
            inclusive: !0,
            exact: !1,
            message: a.minSize.message
        }), r.dirty()),
        a.maxSize !== null && n.data.size > a.maxSize.value && (Re(n, {
            code: Se.too_big,
            maximum: a.maxSize.value,
            type: "set",
            inclusive: !0,
            exact: !1,
            message: a.maxSize.message
        }), r.dirty());
        const i = this._def.valueType;
        function o(c) {
            const d = new Set;
            for (const u of c) {
                if (u.status === "aborted")
                    return it;
                u.status === "dirty" && r.dirty(),
                d.add(u.value)
            }
            return {
                status: r.value,
                value: d
            }
        }
        const l = [...n.data.values()].map((c, d) => i._parse(new Ta(n, c, n.path, d)));
        return n.common.async ? Promise.all(l).then(c => o(c)) : o(l)
    }
    min(s, r)
    {
        return new fl({
            ...this._def,
            minSize: {
                value: s,
                message: Ke.toString(r)
            }
        })
    }
    max(s, r)
    {
        return new fl({
            ...this._def,
            maxSize: {
                value: s,
                message: Ke.toString(r)
            }
        })
    }
    size(s, r)
    {
        return this.min(s, r).max(s, r)
    }
    nonempty(s)
    {
        return this.min(1, s)
    }
}

class oc extends jt {
    constructor()
    {
        super(...arguments),
        this.validate = this.implement
    }
    _parse(s)
    {
        const {ctx: r} = this._processInputParams(s);
        if (r.parsedType !== Le.function)
            return Re(r, {
                code: Se.invalid_type,
                expected: Le.function,
                received: r.parsedType
            }), it;
        function n(l, c) {
            return zf({
                data: l,
                path: r.path,
                errorMaps: [r.common.contextualErrorMap, r.schemaErrorMap, Ff(), zc].filter(d => !!d),
                issueData: {
                    code: Se.invalid_arguments,
                    argumentsError: c
                }
            })
        }
        function a(l, c) {
            return zf({
                data: l,
                path: r.path,
                errorMaps: [r.common.contextualErrorMap, r.schemaErrorMap, Ff(), zc].filter(d => !!d),
                issueData: {
                    code: Se.invalid_return_type,
                    returnTypeError: c
                }
            })
        }
        const i = {
                errorMap: r.common.contextualErrorMap
            },
            o = r.data;
        if (this._def.returns instanceof Vc) {
            const l = this;
            return kr(async function(...c) {
                const d = new hn([]),
                    u = await l._def.args.parseAsync(c, i).catch(y => {
                        throw d.addIssue(n(c, y)), d
                    }),
                    m = await Reflect.apply(o, this, u);
                return await l._def.returns._def.type.parseAsync(m, i).catch(y => {
                    throw d.addIssue(a(m, y)), d
                })
            })
        } else {
            const l = this;
            return kr(function(...c) {
                const d = l._def.args.safeParse(c, i);
                if (!d.success)
                    throw new hn([n(c, d.error)]);
                const u = Reflect.apply(o, this, d.data),
                    m = l._def.returns.safeParse(u, i);
                if (!m.success)
                    throw new hn([a(u, m.error)]);
                return m.data
            })
        }
    }

    {
        return this._def.args
    }
    returnType()
    {
        return this._def.returns
    }

    {

            ...this._def,

        })
    }
    returns(s)
    {
        return new oc({
            ...this._def,
            returns: s
        })
    }
    implement(s)
    {
        return this.parse(s)
    }
    strictImplement(s)
    {
        return this.parse(s)
    }

    {

            args: s || Aa.create([]).rest(Qo.create()),

        })

class ta extends jt {
    innerType()
    {
        return this._def.schema
    }
    sourceType()
    {
        return this._def.schema._def.typeName === nt.ZodEffects ? this._def.schema.sourceType() : this._def.schema
    }
    _parse(s)
    {
        const {status: r, ctx: n} = this._processInputParams(s),
            a = this._def.effect || null,
            i = {
                addIssue: o => {
                    Re(n, o),
                    o.fatal ? r.abort() : r.dirty()
                },
                get path() {
                    return n.path
                }
            };
        if (i.addIssue = i.addIssue.bind(i), a.type === "preprocess") {
            const o = a.transform(n.data, i);
            if (n.common.async)
                return Promise.resolve(o).then(async l => {
                    if (r.value === "aborted")
                        return it;
                    const c = await this._def.schema._parseAsync({
                        data: l,
                        path: n.path,
                        parent: n
                    });
                    return c.status === "aborted" ? it : c.status === "dirty" || r.value === "dirty" ? Kl(c.value) : c
                });
            {
                if (r.value === "aborted")
                    return it;
                const l = this._def.schema._parseSync({
                    data: o,
                    path: n.path,
                    parent: n
                });
                return l.status === "aborted" ? it : l.status === "dirty" || r.value === "dirty" ? Kl(l.value) : l
            }
        }
        if (a.type === "refinement") {
            const o = l => {
                const c = a.refinement(l, i);
                if (n.common.async)
                    return Promise.resolve(c);
                if (c instanceof Promise)
                    throw new Error("Async refinement encountered during synchronous parse operation. Use .parseAsync instead.");
                return l
            };
            if (n.common.async === !1) {
                const l = this._def.schema._parseSync({
                    data: n.data,
                    path: n.path,
                    parent: n
                });
                return l.status === "aborted" ? it : (l.status === "dirty" && r.dirty(), o(l.value), {
                    status: r.value,
                    value: l.value
                })
            } else
                return this._def.schema._parseAsync({
                    data: n.data,
                    path: n.path,
                    parent: n
                }).then(l => l.status === "aborted" ? it : (l.status === "dirty" && r.dirty(), o(l.value).then(() => ({
                    status: r.value,
                    value: l.value
                }))))
        }
        if (a.type === "transform")
            if (n.common.async === !1) {
                const o = this._def.schema._parseSync({
                    data: n.data,
                    path: n.path,
                    parent: n
                });
                if (!ml(o))
                    return o;
                const l = a.transform(o.value, i);
                if (l instanceof Promise)
                    throw new Error("Asynchronous transform encountered during synchronous parse operation. Use .parseAsync instead.");
                return {
                    status: r.value,
                    value: l
                }
            } else
                return this._def.schema._parseAsync({
                    data: n.data,
                    path: n.path,
                    parent: n
                }).then(o => ml(o) ? Promise.resolve(a.transform(o.value, i)).then(l => ({
                    status: r.value,
                    value: l
                })) : o);
        kt.assertNever(a)
    }
}
