function R7({value: t=[], onChange: s, maxImages: r=5, maxSizeBytes: n=5 * 1024 * 1024, acceptedTypes: a=["image/jpeg", "image/jpg", "image/png", "image/webp"], className: i, disabled: o=!1}) {
    const [l, c] = h.useState(!1),
        [d, u] = h.useState(t),
        m = h.useRef(null),
        f = async x => {
            const j = Array.from(x.target.files || []);
            if (j.length !== 0) {
                if (d.length + j.length > r) {
                    alert(`Solo se pueden subir un máximo de ${r} imágenes`);
                    return
                }
                c(!0);
                try {
                    const b = [],
                        p = [];
                    for (const w of j) {
                        if (!a.includes(w.type)) {
                            alert(`Tipo de archivo no válido: ${w.type}. Solo se permiten: ${a.join(", ")}`);
                            continue
                        }
                        if (w.size > n) {
                            alert(`El archivo ${w.name} es demasiado grande. Máximo: ${n / (1024 * 1024)}MB`);
                            continue
                        }
                        const C = URL.createObjectURL(w);
                        p.push(C);
                        const E = new FormData;
                        E.append("image", w);
                        const k = await fetch("/api/upload-image", {
                            method: "POST",
                            body: E
                        });
                        if (k.ok) {
                            const D = await k.json();
                            b.push(D.imageUrl)
                        } else
                            console.error("Error uploading image:", w.name),
                            URL.revokeObjectURL(C)
                    }
                    const v = [...t, ...b],
                        N = [...d, ...p];
                    s(v),
                    u(N)
                } catch (b) {
                    console.error("Error uploading images:", b)
                } finally {
                    c(!1),
                    m.current && (m.current.value = "")
                }
            }
        },
        y = x => {
            const j = t.filter((v, N) => N !== x),
                b = d.filter((v, N) => N !== x),
                p = d[x];
            p && p.startsWith("blob:") && URL.revokeObjectURL(p),
            s(j),
            u(b)
        },
        g = () => {
            var x;
            (x = m.current) == null || x.click()
        };
    return e.jsxs("div", {
        className: ue("space-y-4", i),
        children: [e.jsx(V, {
            className: "border-dashed",
            children: e.jsx(U, {
                className: "p-6",
                children: e.jsxs("div", {
                    className: "text-center",
                    children: [e.jsx(Us, {
                        className: "mx-auto h-12 w-12 text-muted-foreground/50 mb-4"
                    }), e.jsxs("p", {
                        className: "text-sm text-muted-foreground mb-4",
                        children: ["Subir imágenes del vehículo (", d.length, "/", r, ")"]
                    }), e.jsx("input", {
                        ref: m,
                        type: "file",
                        multiple: !0,
                        accept: a.join(","),
                        onChange: f,
                        className: "hidden",
                        disabled: o || l || d.length >= r
                    }), e.jsxs(M, {
                        type: "button",
                        variant: "outline",
                        onClick: g,
                        disabled: o || l || d.length >= r,
                        className: "w-full",
                        children: [e.jsx(ci, {
                            className: "h-4 w-4 mr-2"
                        }), l ? "Subiendo..." : "Seleccionar imágenes"]
                    }), e.jsxs("p", {
                        className: "text-xs text-muted-foreground mt-2",
                        children: ["Máximo ", r, " imágenes, ", n / (1024 * 1024), "MB por imagen"]
                    })]
                })
            })
        }), d.length > 0 && e.jsx("div", {
            className: "grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-3 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-4",
            children: d.map((x, j) => e.jsx("div", {
                className: "relative group",
                children: e.jsx(V, {
                    children: e.jsx(U, {
                        className: "p-2",
                        children: e.jsxs("div", {
                            className: "relative aspect-square",
                            children: [e.jsx("img", {
                                src: x,
                                alt: `Imagen ${j + 1}`,
                                className: "w-full h-full object-cover rounded"
                            }), e.jsx(M, {
                                type: "button",
                                variant: "destructive",
                                size: "sm",
                                className: "absolute top-1 right-1 h-6 w-6 p-0 opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 transition-opacity",
                                onClick: () => y(j),
                                disabled: o || l,
                                children: e.jsx(er, {
                                    className: "h-3 w-3"
                                })
                            })]
                        })
                    })
                })
            }, j))
        })]
    })
}

function H7(t, s) {
    return `${Math.round(t / s * 100)}%`
}
function BT(t, s) {
    return t == null ? "indeterminate" : t === s ? "complete" : "loading"
}
function Hf(t) {
    return typeof t == "number"
}
function b1(t) {
    return Hf(t) && !isNaN(t) && t > 0
}
function N1(t, s) {
    return Hf(t) && !isNaN(t) && t <= s && t >= 0
}
function W7(t, s) {
    return `Invalid prop \`max\` of value \`${t}\` supplied to \`${s}\`. Only numbers greater than 0 are valid max values. Defaulting to \`${H0}\`.`
}

function ct(t) {

    return t instanceof Date || typeof t == "object" && s === "[object Date]" ? new t.constructor(+t) : typeof t == "number" || s === "[object Number]" || typeof t == "string" || s === "[object String]" ? new Date(t) : new Date(NaN)

}

            c = Array.isArray(l) ? kU(l, m => m.test(o)) : EU(l, m => m.test(o));

        d = t.valueCallback ? t.valueCallback(c) : c,
        d = r.valueCallback ? r.valueCallback(d) : d;
        const u = s.slice(o.length);
        return {
            value: d,
            rest: u
        }
    }
}
function EU(t, s) {
    for (const r in t)
        if (Object.prototype.hasOwnProperty.call(t, r) && s(t[r]))
            return r
}
function kU(t, s) {
    for (let r = 0; r < t.length; r++)
        if (s(t[r]))
            return r
}
function YT(t) {
    return (s, r={}) => {
        const n = s.match(t.matchPattern);
        if (!n)
            return null;
        const a = n[0],
            i = s.match(t.parsePattern);
        if (!i)
            return null;
        let o = t.valueCallback ? t.valueCallback(i[0]) : i[0];
        o = r.valueCallback ? r.valueCallback(o) : o;
        const l = s.slice(a.length);
        return {
            value: o,
            rest: l
        }
    }
}
const PU = /^(\d+)(th|st|nd|rd)?/i,
    _U = /\d+/i,
    TU = {
        narrow: /^(b|a)/i,
        abbreviated: /^(b\.?\s?c\.?|b\.?\s?c\.?\s?e\.?|a\.?\s?d\.?|c\.?\s?e\.?)/i,
        wide: /^(before christ|before common era|anno domini|common era)/i
    },
    AU = {
        any: [/^b/i, /^(a|c)/i]
    },
    MU = {
        narrow: /^[1234]/i,
        abbreviated: /^q[1234]/i,
        wide: /^[1234](th|st|nd|rd)? quarter/i
    },
    RU = {
        any: [/1/i, /2/i, /3/i, /4/i]
    },
    IU = {
        narrow: /^[jfmasond]/i,
        abbreviated: /^(jan|feb|mar|apr|may|jun|jul|aug|sep|oct|nov|dec)/i,
        wide: /^(january|february|march|april|may|june|july|august|september|october|november|december)/i
    },
    DU = {
        narrow: [/^j/i, /^f/i, /^m/i, /^a/i, /^m/i, /^j/i, /^j/i, /^a/i, /^s/i, /^o/i, /^n/i, /^d/i],
        any: [/^ja/i, /^f/i, /^mar/i, /^ap/i, /^may/i, /^jun/i, /^jul/i, /^au/i, /^s/i, /^o/i, /^n/i, /^d/i]
    },
    OU = {
        narrow: /^[smtwf]/i,
        short: /^(su|mo|tu|we|th|fr|sa)/i,
        abbreviated: /^(sun|mon|tue|wed|thu|fri|sat)/i,
        wide: /^(sunday|monday|tuesday|wednesday|thursday|friday|saturday)/i
    },
    LU = {
        narrow: [/^s/i, /^m/i, /^t/i, /^w/i, /^t/i, /^f/i, /^s/i],
        any: [/^su/i, /^m/i, /^tu/i, /^w/i, /^th/i, /^f/i, /^sa/i]
    },
    FU = {
        narrow: /^(a|p|mi|n|(in the|at) (morning|afternoon|evening|night))/i,
        any: /^([ap]\.?\s?m\.?|midnight|noon|(in the|at) (morning|afternoon|evening|night))/i
    },
    zU = {
        any: {
            am: /^a/i,
            pm: /^p/i,
            midnight: /^mi/i,
            noon: /^no/i,
            morning: /morning/i,
            afternoon: /afternoon/i,
            evening: /evening/i,
            night: /night/i
        }
    },
    $U = {
        ordinalNumber: YT({
            matchPattern: PU,
            parsePattern: _U,
            valueCallback: t => parseInt(t, 10)
        }),
        era: ga({
            matchPatterns: TU,
            defaultMatchWidth: "wide",
            parsePatterns: AU,
            defaultParseWidth: "any"
        }),
        quarter: ga({
            matchPatterns: MU,
            defaultMatchWidth: "wide",
            parsePatterns: RU,
            defaultParseWidth: "any",
            valueCallback: t => t + 1
        }),
        month: ga({
            matchPatterns: IU,
            defaultMatchWidth: "wide",
            parsePatterns: DU,
            defaultParseWidth: "any"
        }),
        day: ga({
            matchPatterns: OU,
            defaultMatchWidth: "wide",
            parsePatterns: LU,
            defaultParseWidth: "any"
        }),
        dayPeriod: ga({
            matchPatterns: FU,
            defaultMatchWidth: "any",
            parsePatterns: zU,
            defaultParseWidth: "any"
        })
    },
    Q0 = {
        code: "en-US",
        formatDistance: uU,
        formatLong: pU,
        formatRelative: gU,
        localize: SU,
        match: $U,
        options: {
            weekStartsOn: 0,
            firstWeekContainsDate: 1
        }
    };
function VU(t) {
    const s = ct(t);
    return ya(s, GT(s)) + 1

function QT(t) {

        r = +pl(s) - +Z7(s);
    return Math.round(r / G0) + 1

function ZT(t, s) {
    var u,
        m,
        f,
        y;
    const r = ct(t),
        n = r.getFullYear(),
        a = ad(),
        i = (s == null ? void 0 : s.firstWeekContainsDate) ?? ((m = (u = s == null ? void 0 : s.locale) == null ? void 0 : u.options) == null ? void 0 : m.firstWeekContainsDate) ?? a.firstWeekContainsDate ?? ((y = (f = a.locale) == null ? void 0 : f.options) == null ? void 0 : y.firstWeekContainsDate) ?? 1,
        o = Qr(t, 0);
    o.setFullYear(n + 1, 0, i),
    o.setHours(0, 0, 0, 0);
    const l = Ma(o, s),
        c = Qr(t, 0);
    c.setFullYear(n, 0, i),
    c.setHours(0, 0, 0, 0);
    const d = Ma(c, s);
    return r.getTime() >= l.getTime() ? n + 1 : r.getTime() >= d.getTime() ? n : n - 1
}
function UU(t, s) {
    var l,
        c,
        d,
        u;

        n = (s == null ? void 0 : s.firstWeekContainsDate) ?? ((u = (d = r.locale) == null ? void 0 : d.options) == null ? void 0 : u.firstWeekContainsDate) ?? 1,
        a = ZT(t, s),
        i = Qr(t, 0);
    return i.setFullYear(a, 0, n), i.setHours(0, 0, 0, 0), Ma(i, s)

        n = +Ma(r, s) - +UU(r, s);

function Lt(t, s) {
    const r = t < 0 ? "-" : "",
        n = Math.abs(t).toString().padStart(s, "0");
    return r + n

function S1(t, s="") {
    const r = t > 0 ? "-" : "+",
        n = Math.abs(t),
        a = Math.trunc(n / 60),
        i = n % 60;
    return i === 0 ? r + String(a) : r + String(a) + s + Lt(i, 2)
}
function E1(t, s) {
    return t % 60 === 0 ? (t > 0 ? "-" : "+") + Lt(Math.abs(t) / 60, 2) : Ao(t, s)
}
function Ao(t, s="") {
    const r = t > 0 ? "-" : "+",
        n = Math.abs(t),
        a = Lt(Math.trunc(n / 60), 2),
        i = Lt(n % 60, 2);
    return r + a + s + i
}
const k1 = (t, s) => {
        switch (t) {
        case "P":
            return s.date({
                width: "short"
            });
        case "PP":
            return s.date({
                width: "medium"
            });
        case "PPP":
            return s.date({
                width: "long"
            });
        case "PPPP":
        default:
            return s.date({
                width: "full"
            })
        }
    },
    JT = (t, s) => {
        switch (t) {
        case "p":
            return s.time({
                width: "short"
            });
        case "pp":
            return s.time({
                width: "medium"
            });
        case "ppp":
            return s.time({
                width: "long"
            });
        case "pppp":
        default:
            return s.time({
                width: "full"
            })
        }
    },
    qU = (t, s) => {
        const r = t.match(/(P+)(p+)?/) || [],

            a = r[2];
        if (!a)
            return k1(t, s);
        let i;
        switch (n) {
        case "P":
            i = s.dateTime({
                width: "short"
            });
            break;
        case "PP":
            i = s.dateTime({
                width: "medium"
            });
            break;
        case "PPP":
            i = s.dateTime({
                width: "long"
            });
            break;
        case "PPPP":
        default:
            i = s.dateTime({
                width: "full"
            });
            break
        }
        return i.replace("{{date}}", k1(n, s)).replace("{{time}}", JT(a, s))
    },
    BU = {
        p: JT,
        P: qU
    },
    HU = /^D+$/,
    WU = /^Y+$/,
    GU = ["D", "DD", "YY", "YYYY"];
function KU(t) {
    return HU.test(t)
}
function YU(t) {
    return WU.test(t)
}
function QU(t, s, r) {
    const n = ZU(t, s, r);
    if (console.warn(n), GU.includes(t))
        throw new RangeError(n)
}
function ZU(t, s, r) {
    const n = t[0] === "Y" ? "years" : "days of the month";
    return `Use \`${t.toLowerCase()}\` instead of \`${t}\` (in \`${s}\`) for formatting ${n} to the input \`${r}\`; see: https://github.com/date-fns/date-fns/blob/master/docs/unicodeTokens.md`
}
const XU = /[yYQqMLwIdDecihHKkms]o|(\w)\1*|''|'(''|[^'])+('|$)|./g,
    JU = /P+p+|P+|p+|''|'(''|[^'])+('|$)|./g,
    eq = /^'([^]*?)'?$/,
    tq = /''/g,
    sq = /[a-zA-Z]/;
function Bt(t, s, r) {
    var u,
        m,
        f,
        y,
        g,
        x,
        j,
        b;
    const n = ad(),
        a = (r == null ? void 0 : r.locale) ?? n.locale ?? Q0,
        i = (r == null ? void 0 : r.firstWeekContainsDate) ?? ((m = (u = r == null ? void 0 : r.locale) == null ? void 0 : u.options) == null ? void 0 : m.firstWeekContainsDate) ?? n.firstWeekContainsDate ?? ((y = (f = n.locale) == null ? void 0 : f.options) == null ? void 0 : y.firstWeekContainsDate) ?? 1,
        o = (r == null ? void 0 : r.weekStartsOn) ?? ((x = (g = r == null ? void 0 : r.locale) == null ? void 0 : g.options) == null ? void 0 : x.weekStartsOn) ?? n.weekStartsOn ?? ((b = (j = n.locale) == null ? void 0 : j.options) == null ? void 0 : b.weekStartsOn) ?? 0,
        l = ct(t);
    if (!sU(l))
        throw new RangeError("Invalid time value");
    let c = s.match(JU).map(p => {
        const v = p[0];
        if (v === "p" || v === "P") {
            const N = BU[v];
            return N(p, a.formatLong)
        }
        return p
    }).join("").match(XU).map(p => {
        if (p === "''")
            return {
                isToken: !1,
                value: "'"
            };
        const v = p[0];
        if (v === "'")
            return {
                isToken: !1,
                value: rq(p)
            };
        if (C1[v])
            return {
                isToken: !0,
                value: p
            };
        if (v.match(sq))
            throw new RangeError("Format string contains an unescaped latin alphabet character `" + v + "`");
        return {
            isToken: !1,
            value: p
        }
    });
    a.localize.preprocessor && (c = a.localize.preprocessor(l, c));
    const d = {
        firstWeekContainsDate: i,
        weekStartsOn: o,
        locale: a
    };
    return c.map(p => {
        if (!p.isToken)
            return p.value;
        const v = p.value;
        (!(r != null && r.useAdditionalWeekYearTokens) && YU(v) || !(r != null && r.useAdditionalDayOfYearTokens) && KU(v)) && QU(v, s, String(t));
        const N = C1[v[0]];
        return N(l, v, a.localize, d)
    }).join("")
}
function rq(t) {
    const s = t.match(eq);
    return s ? s[1].replace(tq, "'") : t
}
function nq(t, s, r) {
    const n = ad(),
        a = (r == null ? void 0 : r.locale) ?? n.locale ?? Q0,
        i = 2520,
        o = Lh(t, s);
    if (isNaN(o))
        throw new RangeError("Invalid time value");
    const l = Object.assign({}, r, {
        addSuffix: r == null ? void 0 : r.addSuffix,
        comparison: o
    });
    let c,
        d;
    o > 0 ? (c = ct(s), d = ct(t)) : (c = ct(t), d = ct(s));
    const u = cU(d, c),
        m = (qc(d) - qc(c)) / 1e3,
        f = Math.round((u - m) / 60);
    let y;
    if (f < 2)
        return r != null && r.includeSeconds ? u < 5 ? a.formatDistance("lessThanXSeconds", 5, l) : u < 10 ? a.formatDistance("lessThanXSeconds", 10, l) : u < 20 ? a.formatDistance("lessThanXSeconds", 20, l) : u < 40 ? a.formatDistance("halfAMinute", 0, l) : u < 60 ? a.formatDistance("lessThanXMinutes", 1, l) : a.formatDistance("xMinutes", 1, l) : f === 0 ? a.formatDistance("lessThanXMinutes", 1, l) : a.formatDistance("xMinutes", f, l);
    if (f < 45)
        return a.formatDistance("xMinutes", f, l);
    if (f < 90)
        return a.formatDistance("aboutXHours", 1, l);
    if (f < w1) {
        const g = Math.round(f / 60);
        return a.formatDistance("aboutXHours", g, l)
    } else {
        if (f < i)
            return a.formatDistance("xDays", 1, l);
        if (f < mh) {
            const g = Math.round(f / w1);
            return a.formatDistance("xDays", g, l)
        } else if (f < mh * 2)
            return y = Math.round(f / mh), a.formatDistance("aboutXMonths", y, l)
    }
    if (y = lU(d, c), y < 12) {
        const g = Math.round(f / mh);
        return a.formatDistance("xMonths", g, l)
    } else {
        const g = y % 12,
            x = Math.trunc(y / 12);
        return g < 3 ? a.formatDistance("aboutXYears", x, l) : g < 9 ? a.formatDistance("overXYears", x, l) : a.formatDistance("almostXYears", x + 1, l)
    }
}
function aq(t, s) {
    return nq(t, tU(t), s)
}
function iq(t) {
    const s = ct(t),
        r = s.getFullYear(),
        n = s.getMonth(),
        a = Qr(t, 0);
    return a.setFullYear(r, n + 1, 0), a.setHours(0, 0, 0, 0), a.getDate()
}
function oq(t) {
    return Math.trunc(+ct(t) / 1e3)
}
function lq(t) {
    const s = ct(t),
        r = s.getMonth();
    return s.setFullYear(s.getFullYear(), r + 1, 0), s.setHours(0, 0, 0, 0), s
}
function cq(t, s) {
    return rU(lq(t), Wr(t), s) + 1
}
function py(t, s) {
    const r = ct(t),
        n = ct(s);
    return r.getTime() > n.getTime()
}
function eA(t, s) {
    const r = ct(t),
        n = ct(s);
    return +r < +n
}
function Z0(t, s) {
    const r = ct(t),
        n = ct(s);
    return r.getFullYear() === n.getFullYear() && r.getMonth() === n.getMonth()
}
function dq(t, s) {
    const r = ct(t),
        n = ct(s);
    return r.getFullYear() === n.getFullYear()
}
function fg(t, s) {
    return jr(t, -s)
}
function pg(t, s) {
    const r = ct(t),
        n = r.getFullYear(),
        a = r.getDate(),
        i = Qr(t, 0);
    i.setFullYear(n, s, 15),
    i.setHours(0, 0, 0, 0);
    const o = iq(i);
    return r.setMonth(s, Math.min(a, o)), r
}
function P1(t, s) {
    const r = ct(t);
    return isNaN(+r) ? Qr(t, NaN) : (r.setFullYear(s), r)
}

    T1 = t => {
        switch (t.toLowerCase()) {
        case "completed":
            return "bg-green-100 text-green-800 dark:bg-green-900 dark:text-green-100";
        case "failed":
            return "bg-red-100 text-red-800 dark:bg-red-900 dark:text-red-100";
        case "partial":
            return "bg-yellow-100 text-yellow-800 dark:bg-yellow-900 dark:text-yellow-100";
        case "processing":
            return "bg-blue-100 text-blue-800 dark:bg-blue-900 dark:text-blue-100";
        default:
            return "bg-gray-100 text-gray-800 dark:bg-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300"
        }
    },
    A1 = t => {
        switch (t) {
        case "vehicles":
            return "Vehículos";
        case "parts":
            return "Piezas";
        case "all":
            return "Vehículos y Piezas";
        default:
            return t
        }
    },
    M1 = t => {
        switch (t.toLowerCase()) {
        case "completed":
            return "Completado";
        case "failed":
            return "Fallido";
        case "partial":
            return "Parcial";
        case "processing":
        case "in_progress":
            return "En progreso";
        case "paused":
            return "Pausado";
        case "cancelled":
            return "Cancelado";
        default:
            return t
        }
    },
    qq = t => (t.status === "failed" || t.status === "partial" || t.status === "paused") && t.details && (t.details.lastId || t.details.vehicles && t.details.vehicles.lastId || t.details.parts && t.details.parts.lastId),
    Bq = t => t.status === "processing" || t.status === "in_progress",
    Hq = t => t.status === "processing" || t.status === "in_progress" || t.status === "paused",
    Wq = ({history: t, isLoading: s, onDelete: r, onResume: n, onPause: a, onCancel: i, pageSize: o=10, onDeleteAll: l, onPauseAll: c}) => {
        const [d, u] = h.useState(!1),
            [m, f] = h.useState(null),
            [y, g] = h.useState([]),
            [x, j] = h.useState(!1),
            [b, p] = h.useState(null),
            {toast: v} = tt(),
            N = hr(),
            [w, C] = h.useState(1),
            E = (w - 1) * o,
            k = E + o,
            D = t.slice(E, k),
            K = Math.ceil(t.length / o),
            L = async () => {
                if (b !== "delete-all") {
                    p("delete-all");
                    try {
                        const O = t.filter(ee => ee.status === "in_progress" || ee.status === "processing");
                        for (const ee of O)
                            try {
                                await ss.cancelImport(ee.id)
                            } catch (ge) {
                                console.error(`Error al cancelar importación ${ee.id}:`, ge)
                            }
                        const S = await fetch("/api/import/history", {
                            method: "DELETE",
                            headers: {
                                "Content-Type": "application/json"
                            },
                            credentials: "include"
                        });
                        if (!S.ok)
                            throw new Error("Error al eliminar historial");
                        const B = await S.json();
                        v({
                            title: "Eliminado correctamente",
                            description: B.message
                        }),
                        l && l()
                    } catch (O) {
                        console.error("Error al eliminar todas las importaciones:", O),
                        v({
                            title: "Error",
                            description: "No se pudo eliminar el historial de importaciones",
                            variant: "destructive"
                        })
                    }
                    p(null)
                }
            },
            R = async () => {
                if (b !== "pause-all") {
                    p("pause-all");
                    try {
                        const O = await fetch("/api/import/history/pause-all", {
                            method: "POST",
                            headers: {
                                "Content-Type": "application/json"
                            }
                        });
                        if (!O.ok)
                            throw new Error("Error al pausar importaciones");
                        const S = await O.json();
                        v({
                            title: "Pausado correctamente",
                            description: S.message
                        }),
                        c && c()
                    } catch (O) {
                        console.error("Error al pausar todas las importaciones:", O),
                        v({
                            title: "Error",
                            description: "No se pudieron pausar las importaciones",
                            variant: "destructive"
                        })
                    }
                    p(null)
                }
            },
            z = O => {
                g(S => S.includes(O) ? S.filter(B => B !== O) : [...S, O])
            },
            H = () => {
                y.length === t.length ? g([]) : g(t.map(O => O.id))
            },
            F = async () => {
                p("bulk-delete");
                let O = 0,
                    S = 0;
                for (const B of y)
                    try {
                        await ss.deleteHistoryItem(B),
                        r && r(B),
                        O++
                    } catch (ee) {
                        console.error(`Error al eliminar registro ${B}:`, ee),
                        S++
                    }
                v({
                    title: "Eliminación masiva completada",
                    description: `${O} registros eliminados. ${S} errores.`,
                    variant: S > 0 ? "destructive" : "default"
                }),
                g([]),
                j(!1),
                p(null)
            },
            A = O => {
                f(O),
                u(!0)
            },
            P = async () => {
                if (m !== null) {
                    try {
                        await ss.deleteHistoryItem(m),
                        r && r(m),
                        v({
                            title: "Eliminado correctamente",
                            description: "El registro ha sido eliminado del historial"
                        })
                    } catch (O) {
                        console.error("Error al eliminar registro:", O),
                        v({
                            title: "Error al eliminar",
                            description: "No se pudo eliminar el registro. Intente nuevamente.",
                            variant: "destructive"
                        })
                    }
                    u(!1),
                    f(null)

            I = async O => {
                p(`resume-${O}`);

                            headers: {
                                "Content-Type": "application/json"
                            }
                        }),
                        B = await S.json();
                    if (S.ok && B.success)
                        v({
                            title: "Importación reanudada",
                            description: B.message || "La importación se ha reanudado correctamente"
                        }),
                        await N.invalidateQueries({
                            queryKey: ["/api/import/history"]
                        });
                    else
                        throw new Error(B.message || "Error al reanudar la importación")
                } catch (S) {
                    console.error("Error reanudando importación:", S),
                    v({
                        title: "Error",
                        description: S instanceof Error ? S.message : "No se pudo reanudar la importación",
                        variant: "destructive"
                    })
                } finally {
                    p(null)
                }
            },
            $ = async O => {
                p(`pause-${O}`);
                try {
                    const S = await fetch(`/api/import/history/${O}/pause`, {
                            method: "POST",
                            headers: {
                                "Content-Type": "application/json"
                            }
                        }),
                        B = await S.json();
                    if (S.ok && B.success)
                        v({
                            title: "Importación pausada",
                            description: B.message || "La importación se ha pausado correctamente"
                        }),
                        await N.invalidateQueries({
                            queryKey: ["/api/import/history"]
                        });

                } catch (S) {
                    console.error("Error pausando importación:", S),
                    v({
                        title: "Error",
                        description: S instanceof Error ? S.message : "No se pudo pausar la importación",
                        variant: "destructive"
                    })
                } finally {
                    p(null)
                }
            },
            ne = async O => {

                    p(`cancel-${O}`);

                            title: "Importación cancelada",
                            description: "La importación se ha cancelado correctamente"
                        }),

                            description: "No se pudo cancelar la importación. Intente nuevamente.",
                            variant: "destructive"

            g = async (x, j=!1) => {
                let b;

                try {
                    b(!0);
                    let p,
                        v;
                    if (x === "all" ? v = "/api/metasync-optimized/import/all" : v = `/api/metasync-optimized/import/${x}`, p = await fetch(v, {
                        method: "POST",
                        headers: {
                            "Content-Type": "application/json"
                        },
                        body: JSON.stringify({
                            fullImport: j,
                            fromDate: f == null ? void 0 : f.toISOString()
                        })
                    }), !p.ok)
                        throw new Error(`Error en la importación: ${p.statusText}`);

function tW() {
    const {toast: t} = tt(),
        s = hr(),
        [r, n] = h.useState(!1),
        {data: a, isLoading: i, error: o} = _e({
            queryKey: ["/api/import/history"],
            select: g => g || []
        }),
        l = rt({
            mutationFn: async () => (n(!0), await Ie("/api/import/recovery", {
                method: "GET"
            })),
            onSuccess: g => {
                var x;
                t({
                    title: "Importaciones recuperadas",
                    description: g.message || `Se han corregido ${((x = g.recoveredImports) == null ? void 0 : x.length) || 0} importaciones`
                }),
                s.invalidateQueries({
                    queryKey: ["/api/import/history"]
                }),
                n(!1)
            },
            onError: g => {
                console.error("Error al recuperar importaciones:", g),
                t({
                    title: "Error",
                    description: "No se pudieron recuperar las importaciones",
                    variant: "destructive"
                }),
                n(!1)
            }
        }),
        c = rt({
            mutationFn: async g => await Ie(`/api/import/recovery/${g}`, {
                method: "POST"
            }),
            onSuccess: g => {
                t({
                    title: "Importación completada",
                    description: `La importación ${g.importId} ha sido marcada como completada`
                }),
                s.invalidateQueries({
                    queryKey: ["/api/import/history"]
                })
            },
            onError: g => {
                console.error("Error al marcar importación como completada:", g),
                t({
                    title: "Error",
                    description: "No se pudo marcar la importación como completada",
                    variant: "destructive"
                })
            }
        }),
        d = g => g ? new Date(g).toLocaleString("es-ES") : "N/A",
        u = (g, x) => {
            if (!g)
                return "N/A";
            const j = new Date(g),
                p = (x ? new Date(x) : new Date).getTime() - j.getTime(),
                v = Math.floor(p / 6e4),
                N = Math.floor(v / 60);
            return N > 0 ? `${N}h ${v % 60}m` : `${v}m`
        },
        m = (a == null ? void 0 : a.filter(g => g.status === "running" && new Date(g.startTime).getTime() < Date.now() - 30 * 60 * 1e3)) || [],
        f = () => {
            l.mutate()
        },
        y = g => {
            c.mutate(g)
        };
    return i ? e.jsx("div", {
        className: "flex items-center justify-center p-6",
        children: e.jsx(Xt, {
            className: "h-8 w-8 animate-spin text-primary"
        })
    }) : o ? e.jsxs(lr, {
        variant: "destructive",
        children: [e.jsx(zr, {
            className: "h-4 w-4"
        }), e.jsx(Zi, {
            children: "Error"
        }), e.jsx(cr, {
            children: "No se pudo cargar el historial de importaciones"
        })]
    }) : e.jsxs(V, {
        className: "w-full",
        children: [e.jsxs(ae, {
            children: [e.jsx(ie, {
                children: "Recuperación de Importaciones"
            }), e.jsx(qt, {
                children: 'Gestiona las importaciones que se han quedado en estado "en progreso"'
            })]
        }), e.jsx(U, {
            children: m.length === 0 ? e.jsxs(lr, {
                children: [e.jsx(It, {
                    className: "h-4 w-4"
                }), e.jsx(Zi, {
                    children: "¡Todo en orden!"
                }), e.jsx(cr, {
                    children: "No hay importaciones bloqueadas en este momento."
                })]
            }) : e.jsxs(e.Fragment, {
                children: [e.jsxs(lr, {
                    variant: "warning",
                    className: "mb-4",
                    children: [e.jsx(zr, {
                        className: "h-4 w-4"
                    }), e.jsx(Zi, {
                        children: "Importaciones bloqueadas"
                    }), e.jsxs(cr, {
                        children: ["Se han detectado ", m.length, ' importaciones que llevan más de 30 minutos en estado "en progreso"']
                    })]
                }), e.jsxs(Ws, {
                    children: [e.jsx(q_, {
                        children: 'Importaciones bloqueadas en estado "en progreso"'
                    }), e.jsx(Gs, {
                        children: e.jsxs(vt, {
                            children: [e.jsx(pe, {
                                children: "ID"
                            }), e.jsx(pe, {
                                children: "Tipo"
                            }), e.jsx(pe, {
                                children: "Inicio"
                            }), e.jsx(pe, {
                                children: "Duración"
                            }), e.jsx(pe, {
                                children: "Estado"
                            }), e.jsx(pe, {
                                children: "Acciones"
                            })]
                        })
                    }), e.jsx(Ks, {
                        children: m.map(g => e.jsxs(vt, {
                            children: [e.jsx(fe, {
                                children: g.id
                            }), e.jsx(fe, {
                                className: "font-medium",
                                children: g.type === "vehicles" ? "Vehículos" : g.type === "parts" ? "Piezas" : g.type === "all" ? "Completa" : g.type
                            }), e.jsx(fe, {
                                children: d(g.startTime)
                            }), e.jsx(fe, {
                                children: u(g.startTime, g.endTime)
                            }), e.jsx(fe, {
                                children: e.jsx(ve, {
                                    variant: "secondary",
                                    className: "bg-yellow-500 hover:bg-yellow-600",
                                    children: "En progreso"
                                })
                            }), e.jsx(fe, {
                                children: e.jsxs(M, {
                                    size: "sm",
                                    onClick: () => y(g.id),
                                    disabled: c.isPending,
                                    children: [c.isPending && c.variables === g.id ? e.jsx(Xt, {
                                        className: "mr-2 h-4 w-4 animate-spin"
                                    }) : null, "Marcar como completada"]
                                })
                            })]
                        }, g.id))
                    })]
                })]
            })
        }), e.jsxs(_a, {
            className: "flex justify-between",
            children: [e.jsx(M, {
                variant: "outline",
                onClick: () => s.invalidateQueries({
                    queryKey: ["/api/import/history"]
                }),
                children: "Actualizar lista"
            }), e.jsxs(M, {
                onClick: f,
                disabled: r || m.length === 0,
                children: [r ? e.jsx(Xt, {
                    className: "mr-2 h-4 w-4 animate-spin"
                }) : null, "Recuperar todas"]
            })]
        })]
    })
}

function Yf(t) {
    return t ? parseInt(t, 10) : 0
}
function JA(t, s) {
    const r = t / s;
    return isNaN(r) ? 0 : r
}
function sx(t) {
    const s = JA(t.viewport, t.content),
        r = t.scrollbar.paddingStart + t.scrollbar.paddingEnd,
        n = (t.scrollbar.size - r) * s;
    return Math.max(n, 18)
}
function xW(t, s, r, n="ltr") {
    const a = sx(r),
        i = a / 2,
        o = s || i,
        l = a - o,
        c = r.scrollbar.paddingStart + o,
        d = r.scrollbar.size - r.scrollbar.paddingEnd - l,
        u = r.content - r.viewport,
        m = n === "ltr" ? [0, u] : [u * -1, 0];
    return eM([c, d], m)(t)
}
function L1(t, s, r="ltr") {
    const n = sx(s),
        a = s.scrollbar.paddingStart + s.scrollbar.paddingEnd,
        i = s.scrollbar.size - a,
        o = s.content - s.viewport,
        l = i - n,
        c = r === "ltr" ? [0, o] : [o * -1, 0],
        d = ty(t, c);
    return eM([0, o], [0, l])(d)
}
function eM(t, s) {
    return r => {
        if (t[0] === t[1] || s[0] === s[1])
            return s[0];
        const n = (s[1] - s[0]) / (t[1] - t[0]);
        return s[0] + n * (r - t[0])
    }
}
function tM(t, s) {
    return t > 0 && t < s
}
var gW = (t, s=() => {}) => {
    let r = {
            left: t.scrollLeft,
            top: t.scrollTop
        },
        n = 0;
    return function a() {
        const i = {
                left: t.scrollLeft,
                top: t.scrollTop
            },
            o = r.left !== i.left,
            l = r.top !== i.top;
        (o || l) && s(),
        r = i,
        n = window.requestAnimationFrame(a)
    }(), () => window.cancelAnimationFrame(n)
};
function rx(t, s) {
    const r = Zt(t),
        n = h.useRef(0);
    return h.useEffect(() => () => window.clearTimeout(n.current), []), h.useCallback(() => {
        window.clearTimeout(n.current),
        n.current = window.setTimeout(r, s)
    }, [r, s])

        var Ce,
            be;
        const [, t] = dt(),
            {toast: s} = tt(),
            {user: r} = _s(),
            [n, a] = h.useState(""),
            [i, o] = h.useState(1),
            [l, c] = h.useState(null),
            [d, u] = h.useState(!1),
            [m, f] = h.useState(!1),
            [y, g] = h.useState("fechaActualizacion"),
            [x, j] = h.useState("desc"),
            [b, p] = h.useState(""),
            [v, N] = h.useState("all"),
            [w, C] = h.useState("all"),
            [E, k] = h.useState({
                min: "",
                max: ""
            }),
            [D, K] = h.useState(!1),
            [L, R] = h.useState(!1),
            [z, H] = h.useState(null),
            [F, A] = h.useState(!1),
            [P, I] = h.useState(null);
        ff("/admin/parts/edit/:id"),
        ff("/admin/parts/new"),
        r && !r.isAdmin && t("/");
        const {data: $, isLoading: ne, refetch: O} = _e({
                queryKey: ["/api/search-parts", i, n, b, v, w, E, y, x],
                queryFn: async () => {
                    try {
                        let J = `/api/search-parts?limit=${Ed}&offset=${(i - 1) * Ed}&isAdmin=true&getTotalCount=true`;
                        n && (J += `&q=${encodeURIComponent(n)}`),
                        b && (J += `&familia=${encodeURIComponent(b)}`),
                        v !== "all" && (J += `&activo=${v === "active"}`),
                        w !== "all" && (w === "processed" ? J += "&vehicleType=processed" : w === "associated" && (J += "&vehicleType=associated")),
                        E.min && (J += `&precioMin=${E.min}`),
                        E.max && (J += `&precioMax=${E.max}`),
                        y && (J += `&orden=${y}_${x}`),
                        console.log("Admin parts query URL:", J);
                        const je = await fetch(J, {
                            credentials: "include"
                        });
                        if (!je.ok)
                            throw new Error("Error al cargar piezas");
                        const Be = await je.json();
                        return console.log("Admin parts response:", Be), Be
                    } catch (J) {
                        throw console.error("Error en la consulta de piezas:", J), J
                    }
                },
                enabled: !D && !L
            }),
            {data: S} = _e({
                queryKey: ["/api/optimized/parts/families"],
                queryFn: async () => (await fetch("/api/optimized/parts/families")).json()
            }),
            B = ($ == null ? void 0 : $.data) || [],
            ee = ((Ce = $ == null ? void 0 : $.pagination) == null ? void 0 : Ce.total) || 0,
            ge = ((be = $ == null ? void 0 : $.pagination) == null ? void 0 : be.filtered) || ee,
            Ne = Math.ceil(ge / Ed),
            T = S || [],
            te = rt({
                mutationFn: async J => {
                    const je = await fetch("/api/parts", {
                        method: "POST",
                        headers: {
                            "Content-Type": "application/json"
                        },
                        credentials: "include",
                        body: JSON.stringify(J)
                    });
                    if (!je.ok)
                        throw new Error("Error al crear pieza");
                    return je.json()
                },
                onSuccess: () => {
                    s({
                        title: "Pieza creada",
                        description: "La pieza ha sido creada correctamente"
                    }),
                    rn.invalidateQueries({
                        queryKey: ["/api/search-parts"]
                    }),
                    R(!1),
                    H(null),
                    t("/admin/parts")
                },
                onError: J => {
                    s({
                        title: "Error al crear pieza",
                        description: "No se pudo crear la pieza. Intente nuevamente.",
                        variant: "destructive"
                    })
                }
            }),
            W = rt({
                mutationFn: async ({id: J, data: je}) => {
                    const Be = await fetch(`/api/parts/${J}`, {
                        method: "PUT",
                        headers: {
                            "Content-Type": "application/json"
                        },
                        credentials: "include",
                        body: JSON.stringify(je)
                    });
                    if (!Be.ok)
                        throw new Error("Error al actualizar pieza");
                    return Be.json()
                },
                onSuccess: () => {
                    s({
                        title: "Pieza actualizada",
                        description: "La pieza ha sido actualizada correctamente"
                    }),
                    rn.invalidateQueries({
                        queryKey: ["/api/search-parts"]
                    }),
                    K(!1),
                    H(null),
                    t("/admin/parts")
                },
                onError: J => {
                    s({
                        title: "Error al actualizar pieza",
                        description: "No se pudo actualizar la pieza. Intente nuevamente.",
                        variant: "destructive"
                    })
                }
            }),

                mutationFn: async J => {
                    const je = await fetch(`/api/parts/${J}`, {
                        method: "DELETE",
                        credentials: "include"
                    });

                        throw new Error("Error al eliminar pieza");
                    return je.json()
                },

                        const S = await fetch("/api/users");
                        if (!S.ok) {
                            const ge = await S.json();
                            throw new Error(ge.error || "Error al cargar usuarios")
                        }
                        const B = await S.json();
                        return console.log("Usuarios cargados:", B), B.filter(ge => ge.role === "manager" || ge.role === "admin" || ge.isAdmin) || []
                    } catch (S) {
                        throw console.error("Error en la consulta de usuarios:", S), S
                    }
                }
            }),
            R = rt({
                mutationFn: async S => {
                    const B = await fetch("/api/users", {
                        method: "POST",
                        headers: {
                            "Content-Type": "application/json"
                        },
                        body: JSON.stringify(S)
                    });
                    if (!B.ok) {
                        const ee = await B.json();
                        throw new Error(ee.error || "Error al crear usuario")
                    }
                    return B.json()
                },
                onSuccess: () => {
                    s({
                        title: "Usuario creado",
                        description: "El usuario ha sido creado correctamente"
                    }),

                    f(""),
                    g(""),
                    j(""),

                },

                        title: "Error",

                        variant: "destructive"
                    })
                }
            }),
            z = rt({
                mutationFn: async ({id: S, userData: B}) => {
                    const ee = await fetch(`/api/users/${S}`, {
                        method: "PUT",
                        headers: {
                            "Content-Type": "application/json"
                        },
                        body: JSON.stringify(B)
                    });

                    }

    RW = () => {

            [j, b] = h.useState(null),

            {toast: N} = tt(),
            w = hr(),
            {data: C, isLoading: E} = _e({
                queryKey: ["/api/admin/clients"],
                queryFn: async () => {
                    const S = await fetch("/api/admin/clients");
                    if (!S.ok)
                        throw new Error("Error al cargar clientes");
                    return (await S.json()).filter(ee => ee.role === "customer" && !ee.isAdmin)
                }
            }),
            {data: k, isLoading: D} = _e({
                queryKey: ["/api/admin/guest-orders"],
                queryFn: async () => {
                    const S = await fetch("/api/admin/guest-orders");
                    if (!S.ok)
                        throw new Error("Error al cargar pedidos de invitados");
                    return S.json()
                }
            }),
            K = (C == null ? void 0 : C.filter(S => {
                const B = S.firstName.toLowerCase().includes(t.toLowerCase()) || S.lastName.toLowerCase().includes(t.toLowerCase()) || S.email.toLowerCase().includes(t.toLowerCase()) || S.username.toLowerCase().includes(t.toLowerCase()),
                    ee = r === "all" || S.province === r;
                return B && ee
            })) || [],
            L = (k == null ? void 0 : k.filter(S => S.guestName.toLowerCase().includes(a.toLowerCase()) || S.guestEmail.toLowerCase().includes(a.toLowerCase()) || S.orderNumber.toLowerCase().includes(a.toLowerCase()))) || [],
            R = [...new Set(C == null ? void 0 : C.map(S => S.province).filter(Boolean))],
            z = S => {
                switch (S) {
                case "admin":
                    return "destructive";
                case "manager":
                    return "secondary";
                case "customer":
                    return "default";
                default:
                    return "outline"
                }

            H = S => {
                switch (S) {
                case "admin":
                    return "Administrador";
                case "manager":
                    return "Gestor";
                case "customer":
                    return "Cliente";
                default:
                    return S
                }
            },

                            firstName: B.firstName,
                            lastName: B.lastName,
                            email: B.email,
                            phone: B.phone,
                            address: B.address,
                            city: B.city,

                        ge = await fetch(`/api/admin/users/${S}`, {

                            },

                        });
                    if (!ge.ok)
                        throw new Error("Error al actualizar cliente");
                    return ge.json()
                },
                onSuccess: () => {
                    w.invalidateQueries({
                        queryKey: ["/api/admin/clients"]
                    }),

                        description: "Los datos del cliente se han actualizado correctamente"
                    }),
                    y(!1),

                    }),

                mutationFn: async S => {

                        method: "DELETE"
                    });
                    if (!B.ok)
                        throw new Error("Error al eliminar cliente");
                    return B.json()
                },

                        queryKey: ["/api/admin/clients"]

                        })]
                    })]
                })
            })]
        })
    };
function oi({className: t, ...s}) {
    return e.jsx("div", {
        className: ue("animate-pulse rounded-md bg-muted", t),
        ...s
    })
}
const ja = ({children: t}) => e.jsxs("div", {
    className: "flex min-h-screen bg-gray-100",

function IW({order: t, isOpen: s, onClose: r}) {
    const {toast: n} = tt(),
        a = hr(),
        i = h.useRef(null),
        o = h.useRef(null),
        [l, c] = h.useState({
            transportAgency: (t == null ? void 0 : t.transportAgency) || "",
            expeditionNumber: (t == null ? void 0 : t.expeditionNumber) || "",
            adminObservations: (t == null ? void 0 : t.adminObservations) || "",
            documents: (t == null ? void 0 : t.documents) || [],
            invoicePdf: (t == null ? void 0 : t.invoicePdf) || ""
        }),
        [d, u] = h.useState(!1),
        m = rt({
            mutationFn: p => (console.log("🚀 Frontend: Enviando actualización de pedido:", {
                orderId: t.id,
                url: `/api/admin/orders/${t.id}/update-admin-info`,
                data: p
            }), Ie("PATCH", `/api/admin/orders/${t.id}/update-admin-info`, p)),
            onSuccess: p => {
                console.log("✅ Frontend: Actualización exitosa:", p),
                n({
                    title: "Pedido actualizado",
                    description: "La información adicional se ha guardado correctamente."
                }),
                a.invalidateQueries({
                    queryKey: ["/api/admin/orders"]
                }),
                r()
            },
            onError: p => {
                var v,
                    N,
                    w,
                    C;
                console.error("❌ Frontend: Error al actualizar pedido:", p),
                console.error("❌ Frontend: Error details:", {
                    message: p.message,
                    response: (v = p.response) == null ? void 0 : v.data,
                    status: (N = p.response) == null ? void 0 : N.status
                }),
                n({
                    title: "Error",
                    description: ((C = (w = p.response) == null ? void 0 : w.data) == null ? void 0 : C.error) || p.message || "No se pudo actualizar el pedido.",
                    variant: "destructive"
                })
            }
        }),
        f = async (p, v) => {
            console.log("📤 Iniciando upload de archivo:", {
                fileName: p.name,
                fileSize: p.size,
                orderId: t.id,
                type: v
            });
            const N = new FormData;
            N.append("file", p),
            N.append("orderId", t.id.toString()),
            N.append("type", v);
            try {
                const w = await fetch("/api/upload/order-document", {
                    method: "POST",
                    body: N,
                    credentials: "same-origin"
                });
                if (console.log("📡 Response status:", w.status), !w.ok) {
                    const E = await w.json().catch(() => ({}));
                    throw console.error("❌ Upload error:", {
                        status: w.status,
                        error: E
                    }), new Error(E.error || `Error HTTP ${w.status}: No se pudo subir el archivo`)
                }
                const C = await w.json();
                return console.log("✅ Upload exitoso:", C), C.filePath
            } catch (w) {
                throw console.error("❌ Error en uploadFile:", w), new Error(w.message || "Error al subir archivo")
            }
        },
        y = async p => {
            const v = p.target.files;
            if (v) {
                u(!0);
                try {
                    const N = Array.from(v).map(C => f(C, "document")),
                        w = await Promise.all(N);
                    c(C => ({
                        ...C,
                        documents: [...C.documents, ...w]
                    })),
                    n({
                        title: "Documentos subidos",
                        description: `Se han subido ${v.length} documento(s) correctamente.`
                    })
                } catch (N) {
                    console.error("❌ Error en handleDocumentUpload:", N),
                    n({
                        title: "Error",
                        description: N.message || "Error al subir los documentos.",
                        variant: "destructive"
                    })
                } finally {
                    u(!1),
                    i.current && (i.current.value = "")
                }
            }
        },
        g = async p => {
            var w;
            const v = (w = p.target.files) == null ? void 0 : w[0];
            if (!v)
                return;
            if (!["application/pdf", "image/jpeg", "image/jpg", "image/png"].includes(v.type)) {
                n({
                    title: "Error",
                    description: "Solo se permiten archivos PDF e imágenes (JPG, PNG) para la factura.",
                    variant: "destructive"
                });
                return
            }
            u(!0);
            try {
                const C = await f(v, "invoice");
                c(E => ({
                    ...E,
                    invoicePdf: C
                })),
                n({
                    title: "Factura subida",
                    description: "La factura se ha subido correctamente."
                })
            } catch (C) {
                console.error("❌ Error en handleInvoiceUpload:", C),
                n({
                    title: "Error",
                    description: C.message || "Error al subir la factura.",
                    variant: "destructive"
                })
            } finally {
                u(!1),
                o.current && (o.current.value = "")
            }
        },
        x = p => {
            c(v => ({
                ...v,
                documents: v.documents.filter((N, w) => w !== p)
            }))
        },
        j = () => {
            c(p => ({
                ...p,
                invoicePdf: ""
            }))
        },
        b = p => {
            p.preventDefault(),
            m.mutate(l)
        };
    return t ? e.jsx(Es, {
        open: s,
        onOpenChange: r,
        children: e.jsxs(xs, {
            className: "max-w-2xl max-h-[90vh] overflow-y-auto",
            children: [e.jsx(gs, {
                children: e.jsxs(vs, {
                    children: ["Información Adicional - Pedido ", t.orderNumber]
                })
            }), e.jsxs("form", {
                onSubmit: b,
                className: "space-y-6",
                children: [e.jsxs("div", {
                    className: "bg-gray-50 p-4 rounded-lg",
                    children: [e.jsx("h3", {
                        className: "font-semibold mb-2",
                        children: "Información del Pedido"
                    }), e.jsxs("div", {
                        className: "grid grid-cols-2 gap-4 text-sm",
                        children: [e.jsxs("div", {
                            children: [e.jsx("span", {
                                className: "font-medium",
                                children: "Cliente:"
                            }), " ", t.customerName]
                        }), e.jsxs("div", {
                            children: [e.jsx("span", {
                                className: "font-medium",
                                children: "Email:"
                            }), " ", t.customerEmail]
                        }), e.jsxs("div", {
                            children: [e.jsx("span", {
                                className: "font-medium",
                                children: "Total:"
                            }), " ", t.total, "€"]
                        }), e.jsxs("div", {
                            children: [e.jsx("span", {
                                className: "font-medium",
                                children: "Estado:"
                            }), " ", t.orderStatus]
                        })]
                    })]
                }), e.jsxs("div", {
                    className: "space-y-4",
                    children: [e.jsxs("div", {
                        children: [e.jsx(q, {
                            htmlFor: "transportAgency",
                            children: "Agencia de Transporte"
                        }), e.jsx(se, {
                            id: "transportAgency",
                            value: l.transportAgency,
                            onChange: p => c(v => ({
                                ...v,
                                transportAgency: p.target.value
                            })),
                            placeholder: "Nombre de la agencia de transporte"
                        })]
                    }), e.jsxs("div", {
                        children: [e.jsx(q, {
                            htmlFor: "expeditionNumber",
                            children: "Número de Expedición"
                        }), e.jsx(se, {
                            id: "expeditionNumber",
                            value: l.expeditionNumber,
                            onChange: p => c(v => ({
                                ...v,
                                expeditionNumber: p.target.value
                            })),
                            placeholder: "Número de seguimiento o expedición"
                        })]
                    }), e.jsxs("div", {

                            htmlFor: "adminObservations",
                            children: "Observaciones"
                        }), e.jsx(Ut, {
                            id: "adminObservations",
                            value: l.adminObservations,
                            onChange: p => c(v => ({
                                ...v,
                                adminObservations: p.target.value
                            })),
                            placeholder: "Observaciones adicionales para el cliente...",
                            rows: 4
                        })]
                    }), e.jsxs("div", {

                        }), e.jsxs("div", {

                                onClick: () => {
                                    var p;

                                },

                                className: "hidden"
                            }), l.documents.length > 0 && e.jsx("div", {

                                    className: "flex items-center justify-between bg-gray-50 p-2 rounded",

                                        })]
                                    }), e.jsx(M, {
                                        type: "button",
                                        variant: "ghost",
                                        size: "sm",
                                        onClick: () => x(v),
                                        children: e.jsx(er, {
                                            className: "w-4 h-4"
                                        })
                                    })]
                                }, v))
                            })]
                        })]
                    }), e.jsxs("div", {
                        children: [e.jsx(q, {
                            children: "Factura (PDF o Imagen)"
                        }), e.jsxs("div", {
                            className: "mt-2",
                            children: [e.jsxs(M, {
                                type: "button",
                                variant: "outline",
                                onClick: () => {
                                    var p;
                                    return (p = o.current) == null ? void 0 : p.click()
                                },
                                disabled: d,
                                className: "mb-3",
                                children: [e.jsx(ci, {
                                    className: "w-4 h-4 mr-2"
                                }), d ? "Subiendo..." : "Subir Factura (PDF/Imagen)"]
                            }), e.jsx("input", {
                                ref: o,
                                type: "file",
                                accept: ".pdf,.jpg,.jpeg,.png",
                                onChange: g,
                                className: "hidden"
                            }), l.invoicePdf && e.jsxs("div", {
                                className: "flex items-center justify-between bg-gray-50 p-2 rounded",

                                    }), e.jsx("span", {

                                        children: l.invoicePdf.split("/").pop()

function OW({order: t, isOpen: s, onClose: r}) {
    const [n, a] = h.useState(null),
        [i, o] = h.useState(!1),
        l = async () => {
            if (t != null && t.id) {
                o(!0);
                try {
                    const u = await fetch(`/api/admin/orders/${t.id}`);
                    if (!u.ok)
                        throw new Error("Error al cargar detalles del pedido");
                    const m = await u.json();
                    a(m)
                } catch (u) {
                    console.error("Error al cargar detalles del pedido:", u)
                } finally {
                    o(!1)
                }
            }
        };
    if (h.useEffect(() => {
        s && l()
    }, [s, t == null ? void 0 : t.id]), h.useEffect(() => {
        s && t && l()
    }, [t == null ? void 0 : t.orderStatus, t == null ? void 0 : t.paymentStatus, t == null ? void 0 : t.updatedAt, t == null ? void 0 : t._refetch]), !t)
        return null;
    const c = F1[n == null ? void 0 : n.paymentStatus] || F1.pendiente,
        d = z1[n == null ? void 0 : n.orderStatus] || DW[n == null ? void 0 : n.status] || z1.pendiente_verificar;
    return e.jsx(Es, {
        open: s,
        onOpenChange: r,
        children: e.jsxs(xs, {
            className: "max-w-4xl max-h-[90vh] overflow-y-auto",
            children: [e.jsx(gs, {
                children: e.jsxs(vs, {
                    children: ["Detalles del Pedido #", t.orderNumber]
                })
            }), i ? e.jsx("div", {
                className: "flex items-center justify-center py-8",
                children: e.jsx("div", {
                    className: "animate-spin h-8 w-8 border-4 border-primary border-t-transparent rounded-full"
                })
            }) : n ? e.jsxs("div", {
                className: "space-y-6",
                children: [e.jsxs("div", {

                                    className: "font-semibold",

                                })]

                                })
                            }), e.jsx("p", {

            queryKey: ["/api/admin/orders"]
        }),

            var T,
                te,
                W;

                    if (c === "all")
                        return !0;
                    const re = new Date(S.createdAt),
                        de = new Date;
                    switch (c) {
                    case "today":
                        return re.toDateString() === de.toDateString();
                    case "week":
                        const le = new Date(de.getTime() - 7 * 24 * 60 * 60 * 1e3);
                        return re >= le;
                    case "month":
                        const me = new Date(de.getTime() - 30 * 24 * 60 * 60 * 1e3);
                        return re >= me;
                    default:
                        return !0
                    }
                })();
            return B && ee && ge && Ne
        }), [k, r, a, o, c]),
        R = rt({
            mutationFn: async ({orderId: S, paymentStatus: B}) => Ie(`/api/admin/orders/${S}/payment-status`, {

                }),
                headers: {
                    "Content-Type": "application/json"
                }
            }),

                }),

                            })]
                        }), L.length === 0 && e.jsxs("div", {

                            })]
                        })]
                    })
                })]
            })]
        }), j && g && e.jsx(OW, {
            isOpen: j,
            onClose: () => {
                b(!1),
                x(null)
            },
            order: g
        }), f && u && e.jsx(IW, {

        })]
    })
};
function LW() {
    const {toast: t} = tt(),
        [s, r] = ke.useState([]),
        [n, a] = ke.useState({
            merchantCode: "",
            terminal: "001",
            secretKey: "",
            environment: "test"
        }),
        [i, o] = ke.useState({
            name: "",
            description: "",
            basePrice: "",
            freeShippingThreshold: "",
            weightBasedPricing: !1,
            pricePerKg: "",
            estimatedDays: "1",
            isActive: !0
        });
    ke.useEffect(() => {
        l(),
        c()
    }, []);
    const l = async () => {
            try {
                const m = await Ie("GET", "/api/shipping/methods");
                if (m.ok) {
                    const f = await m.json();
                    r(f)
                }
            } catch (m) {
                console.error("Error loading shipping methods:", m)
            }
        },
        c = async () => {
            try {
                const m = await Ie("GET", "/api/admin/site-config/redsys_config");
                if (m.ok) {
                    const f = await m.json();
                    f.value && a(JSON.parse(f.value))
                }
            } catch (m) {
                console.error("Error loading Redsys config:", m)
            }
        },
        d = async () => {
            try {
                (await Ie("POST", "/api/admin/site-config", {
                    key: "redsys_config",
                    value: JSON.stringify(n),
                    description: "Configuración de Redsys para pagos con tarjeta"
                })).ok && t({
                    title: "Configuración guardada",
                    description: "La configuración de Redsys se ha guardado correctamente"
                })
            } catch {
                t({
                    title: "Error",
                    description: "No se pudo guardar la configuración",
                    variant: "destructive"
                })
            }
        },
        u = async () => {
            try {
                (await Ie("POST", "/api/admin/shipping/methods", {
                    ...i,
                    basePrice: parseFloat(i.basePrice) || 0,
                    freeShippingThreshold: i.freeShippingThreshold ? parseFloat(i.freeShippingThreshold) : null,
                    pricePerKg: parseFloat(i.pricePerKg) || 0,
                    estimatedDays: parseInt(i.estimatedDays) || 1
                })).ok && (t({
                    title: "Método creado",
                    description: "El método de envío se ha creado correctamente"
                }), l(), o({
                    name: "",
                    description: "",
                    basePrice: "",
                    freeShippingThreshold: "",
                    weightBasedPricing: !1,
                    pricePerKg: "",
                    estimatedDays: "1",
                    isActive: !0
                }))
            } catch {
                t({
                    title: "Error",
                    description: "No se pudo crear el método de envío",
                    variant: "destructive"
                })
            }
        };
    return e.jsxs("div", {
        className: "container mx-auto px-4 py-8",
        children: [e.jsx("h1", {
            className: "text-3xl font-bold mb-8",
            children: "Configuración de Pagos y Envíos"
        }), e.jsxs(ls, {
            defaultValue: "shipping",
            className: "space-y-6",
            children: [e.jsxs(es, {
                children: [e.jsx(Ve, {
                    value: "shipping",
                    children: "Métodos de Envío"
                }), e.jsx(Ve, {
                    value: "payments",
                    children: "Configuración de Pagos"
                })]
            }), e.jsxs(ze, {
                value: "shipping",
                className: "space-y-6",
                children: [e.jsxs(V, {
                    children: [e.jsx(ae, {
                        children: e.jsx(ie, {
                            children: "Crear Nuevo Método de Envío"
                        })
                    }), e.jsxs(U, {
                        className: "space-y-4",
                        children: [e.jsxs("div", {
                            className: "grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4",
                            children: [e.jsxs("div", {
                                children: [e.jsx(q, {
                                    htmlFor: "name",
                                    children: "Nombre"
                                }), e.jsx(se, {
                                    id: "name",
                                    value: i.name,
                                    onChange: m => o(f => ({
                                        ...f,
                                        name: m.target.value
                                    })),
                                    placeholder: "Envío estándar"
                                })]
                            }), e.jsxs("div", {
                                children: [e.jsx(q, {
                                    htmlFor: "basePrice",
                                    children: "Precio base (€)"
                                }), e.jsx(se, {
                                    id: "basePrice",
                                    type: "number",
                                    step: "0.01",
                                    value: i.basePrice,
                                    onChange: m => o(f => ({
                                        ...f,
                                        basePrice: m.target.value
                                    })),
                                    placeholder: "5.95"
                                })]
                            }), e.jsxs("div", {
                                children: [e.jsx(q, {
                                    htmlFor: "freeThreshold",
                                    children: "Envío gratuito desde (€)"
                                }), e.jsx(se, {
                                    id: "freeThreshold",
                                    type: "number",
                                    step: "0.01",
                                    value: i.freeShippingThreshold,
                                    onChange: m => o(f => ({
                                        ...f,
                                        freeShippingThreshold: m.target.value
                                    })),
                                    placeholder: "50.00"
                                })]
                            }), e.jsxs("div", {
                                children: [e.jsx(q, {
                                    htmlFor: "estimatedDays",
                                    children: "Días estimados"
                                }), e.jsx(se, {
                                    id: "estimatedDays",
                                    type: "number",
                                    value: i.estimatedDays,
                                    onChange: m => o(f => ({
                                        ...f,
                                        estimatedDays: m.target.value
                                    }))
                                })]
                            })]

                                children: "Descripción"
                            }), e.jsx(se, {
                                id: "description",

                            })]
                        }), e.jsxs("div", {

                        })

                                            })]
                                        })]
                                    }), e.jsx("div", {

                                        children: e.jsx("span", {
                                            className: `px-2 py-1 rounded text-xs ${m.isActive ? "bg-green-100 text-green-800" : "bg-red-100 text-red-800"}`,
                                            children: m.isActive ? "Activo" : "Inactivo"
                                        })
                                    })]
                                })
                            }, m.id))
                        })
                    })]
                })]
            }), e.jsx(ze, {
                value: "payments",
                className: "space-y-6",
                children: e.jsxs(V, {
                    children: [e.jsx(ae, {
                        children: e.jsx(ie, {
                            children: "Configuración de Redsys"
                        })
                    }), e.jsxs(U, {

            })]

}
const FW = {
    bank_transfer: d5,
