function zW() {
    var v,
        N,
        w;
    const {toast: t} = tt(),
        [s, r] = h.useState([]),
        [n, a] = h.useState(!0),
        [i, o] = h.useState(""),
        [l, c] = h.useState({}),
        [d, u] = h.useState(!1),
        [m, f] = h.useState({});
    h.useEffect(() => {
        y()
    }, []);
    const y = async () => {
            try {
                console.log("AdminPaymentMethods: Cargando módulos...");
                const C = await Ie("GET", "/api/admin/payment-modules");
                console.log("AdminPaymentMethods: Response object:", C);
                const E = await C.json();
                if (console.log("AdminPaymentMethods: Data después de JSON:", E), console.log("AdminPaymentMethods: Tipo de data:", typeof E), console.log("AdminPaymentMethods: Es array?", Array.isArray(E)), Array.isArray(E)) {
                    console.log("AdminPaymentMethods: Módulos válidos:", E.length),
                    console.log("AdminPaymentMethods: Primer módulo:", E[0]),
                    r(E);
                    const k = {};
                    E.forEach(D => {
                        k[D.provider] = D.isActive
                    }),
                    f(k),
                    console.log("AdminPaymentMethods: Estados de módulos:", k),
                    E.length > 0 && (o(E[0].provider), c(E[0].config || {}))
                } else
                    console.error("La respuesta no es un array:", E),
                    console.error("AdminPaymentMethods: Tipo de respuesta:", typeof E),
                    r([])
            } catch (C) {
                console.error("AdminPaymentMethods: Error cargando módulos:", C),
                r([]),
                t({
                    title: "Error",
                    description: "No se pudieron cargar los módulos de pago",
                    variant: "destructive"
                })
            } finally {
                a(!1)
            }
        },
        g = C => {
            o(C);
            const E = s.find(k => k.provider === C);
            c((E == null ? void 0 : E.config) || {})
        },
        x = (C, E) => {
            c(k => ({
                ...k,
                [C]: E
            }))
        },
        j = async () => {
            if (i) {
                u(!0);
                try {
                    await Ie("PUT", `/api/admin/payment-modules/${i}`, {
                        config: l
                    }),
                    t({
                        title: "Configuración guardada",
                        description: "La configuración del módulo se ha guardado correctamente"
                    }),
                    await y()
                } catch {
                    t({
                        title: "Error",
                        description: "No se pudo guardar la configuración",
                        variant: "destructive"
                    })
                } finally {
                    u(!1)
                }
            }
        },
        b = async (C, E) => {
            try {
                await Ie("PUT", `/api/admin/payment-modules/${C}`, {
                    isActive: E
                }),
                f(k => ({
                    ...k,
                    [C]: E
                })),
                t({
                    title: E ? "Módulo activado" : "Módulo desactivado",
                    description: `El módulo ${C} ha sido ${E ? "activado" : "desactivado"}`
                }),
                await y()
            } catch {
                t({
                    title: "Error",
                    description: "No se pudo cambiar el estado del módulo",
                    variant: "destructive"
                })
            }
        },
        p = C => {
            var k;
            const E = l[C.name] || "";
            switch (C.type) {
            case "text":
            case "password":
                return e.jsxs("div", {
                    className: "space-y-2",
                    children: [e.jsxs(q, {
                        htmlFor: C.name,
                        className: "text-sm font-medium",
                        children: [C.label, C.required && e.jsx("span", {
                            className: "text-red-500 ml-1",
                            children: "*"
                        })]
                    }), e.jsx(se, {
                        id: C.name,
                        type: C.type,
                        value: E,
                        onChange: D => x(C.name, D.target.value),
                        placeholder: C.description,
                        className: "w-full"
                    }), C.description && e.jsx("p", {
                        className: "text-xs text-muted-foreground",
                        children: C.description
                    })]
                }, C.name);
            case "select":
                return e.jsxs("div", {
                    className: "space-y-2",
                    children: [e.jsxs(q, {
                        htmlFor: C.name,
                        className: "text-sm font-medium",
                        children: [C.label, C.required && e.jsx("span", {
                            className: "text-red-500 ml-1",
                            children: "*"
                        })]
                    }), e.jsx("select", {
                        id: C.name,
                        value: E,
                        onChange: D => x(C.name, D.target.value),
                        className: "w-full p-2 border rounded-md",
                        children: (k = C.options) == null ? void 0 : k.map(D => e.jsx("option", {
                            value: D.value,
                            children: D.label
                        }, D.value))
                    }), C.description && e.jsx("p", {
                        className: "text-xs text-muted-foreground",
                        children: C.description
                    })]
                }, C.name);
            case "checkbox":
                return e.jsxs("div", {
                    className: "flex items-center space-x-2",
                    children: [e.jsx(St, {
                        id: C.name,
                        checked: E,
                        onCheckedChange: D => x(C.name, D)
                    }), e.jsx(q, {
                        htmlFor: C.name,
                        className: "text-sm",
                        children: C.label
                    }), C.description && e.jsxs("p", {
                        className: "text-xs text-muted-foreground ml-2",
                        children: ["(", C.description, ")"]
                    })]
                }, C.name);
            default:
                return null
            }
        };
    return n ? e.jsxs("div", {
        className: "flex min-h-screen bg-background",
        children: [e.jsx(zs, {}), e.jsx("div", {
            className: "flex-1 p-6",
            children: e.jsxs("div", {
                className: "animate-pulse space-y-4",
                children: [e.jsx("div", {
                    className: "h-8 bg-gray-200 rounded w-1/4"
                }), e.jsx("div", {
                    className: "grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-4",
                    children: [1, 2, 3].map(C => e.jsx("div", {
                        className: "h-48 bg-gray-200 rounded"
                    }, C))
                })]
            })
        })]
    }) : (console.log("AdminPaymentMethods: Renderizando con modules:", s, "loading:", n), console.log("AdminPaymentMethods: modules.length:", s.length), e.jsxs("div", {
        className: "flex min-h-screen bg-background",
        children: [e.jsx(zs, {}), e.jsxs("div", {
            className: "flex-1 p-6 space-y-6",
            children: [e.jsx("div", {
                className: "flex justify-between items-center",
                children: e.jsxs("div", {
                    children: [e.jsx("h1", {
                        className: "text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight",
                        children: "Módulos de Pago"
                    }), e.jsx("p", {
                        className: "text-muted-foreground",
                        children: "Gestiona los módulos de pago disponibles en tu tienda"
                    })]
                })
            }), e.jsxs("div", {
                className: "grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-6",
                children: [e.jsx("div", {
                    className: "lg:col-span-1",
                    children: e.jsx("div", {
                        className: "space-y-3",
                        children: s && s.length > 0 ? s.map(C => {
                            const E = FW[C.provider] || ps;
                            return e.jsxs(V, {
                                className: `cursor-pointer transition-all ${i === C.provider ? "ring-2 ring-primary" : "hover:bg-muted/50"}`,
                                onClick: () => g(C.provider),
                                children: [e.jsx(ae, {
                                    className: "pb-3",
                                    children: e.jsxs("div", {
                                        className: "flex items-center justify-between",
                                        children: [e.jsxs("div", {
                                            className: "flex items-center space-x-2",
                                            children: [e.jsx(E, {
                                                className: "h-5 w-5 text-muted-foreground"
                                            }), e.jsx(ie, {
                                                className: "text-sm",
                                                children: C.name
                                            })]
                                        }), e.jsx(ve, {
                                            variant: m[C.provider] ? "default" : "secondary",
                                            children: m[C.provider] ? "Activo" : "Inactivo"
                                        })]
                                    })
                                }), e.jsx(U, {
                                    className: "pt-0",
                                    children: e.jsxs("div", {
                                        className: "flex items-center space-x-2",
                                        children: [e.jsx(St, {
                                            checked: m[C.provider],
                                            onCheckedChange: k => b(C.provider, k),
                                            onClick: k => k.stopPropagation()
                                        }), e.jsx(q, {
                                            className: "text-xs text-muted-foreground",
                                            children: m[C.provider] ? "Habilitado" : "Deshabilitado"
                                        })]
                                    })
                                })]
                            }, C.provider)
                        }) : e.jsxs("div", {
                            className: "text-center py-8",
                            children: [e.jsx(ps, {
                                className: "mx-auto h-12 w-12 text-muted-foreground"
                            }), e.jsx("p", {
                                className: "text-sm text-muted-foreground mt-2",
                                children: "No hay módulos disponibles"
                            })]
                        })
                    })
                }), e.jsx("div", {
                    className: "lg:col-span-3",
                    children: i && e.jsxs(V, {
                        children: [e.jsx(ae, {
                            children: e.jsxs("div", {
                                className: "flex items-center space-x-2",
                                children: [e.jsx(Bs, {
                                    className: "h-5 w-5"
                                }), e.jsxs(ie, {
                                    children: ["Configuración - ", (v = s.find(C => C.provider === i)) == null ? void 0 : v.name]
                                })]
                            })
                        }), e.jsx(U, {
                            className: "space-y-6",
                            children: ((N = s.find(C => C.provider === i)) == null ? void 0 : N.configFields.length) === 0 ? e.jsxs("div", {

                                children: [e.jsx(zr, {
                                    className: "mx-auto h-12 w-12 text-muted-foreground mb-4"
                                }), e.jsx("p", {
                                    className: "text-muted-foreground",

                                })]
                            }) : e.jsxs(e.Fragment, {
                                children: [e.jsx("div", {
                                    className: "grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4",
                                    children: (w = s.find(C => C.provider === i)) == null ? void 0 : w.configFields.map(C => p(C))
                                }), e.jsx("div", {
                                    className: "flex justify-end",
                                    children: e.jsxs(M, {
                                        onClick: j,
                                        disabled: d,
                                        className: "flex items-center space-x-2",
                                        children: [e.jsx(wn, {
                                            className: "h-4 w-4"
                                        }), e.jsx("span", {
                                            children: d ? "Guardando..." : "Guardar Configuración"
                                        })]
                                    })
                                })]
                            })
                        })]
                    })
                })]
            }), s.length === 0 && e.jsxs("div", {
                className: "text-center py-12",
                children: [e.jsx(ps, {
                    className: "mx-auto h-12 w-12 text-muted-foreground"
                }), e.jsx("h3", {
                    className: "mt-2 text-sm font-medium text-gray-900",
                    children: "No hay módulos de pago disponibles"
                }), e.jsx("p", {
                    className: "mt-1 text-sm text-muted-foreground",
                    children: "Los módulos de pago se cargan automáticamente del sistema."
                })]
            })]
        })]
    }))
}
function $W() {
    const {toast: t} = tt(),
        [s, r] = h.useState([]),
        [n, a] = h.useState(!0),
        [i, o] = h.useState(""),
        [l, c] = h.useState({}),
        [d, u] = h.useState(!1);
    h.useEffect(() => {
        m()
    }, []);
    const m = async () => {
            try {
                const v = await Ie("GET", "/api/admin/payment-modules");
                r(v),
                v.length > 0 && (o(v[0].provider), c(v[0].config || {}))
            } catch {
                t({
                    title: "Error",
                    description: "No se pudieron cargar los módulos de pago",
                    variant: "destructive"
                })
            } finally {
                a(!1)
            }
        },
        f = v => {
            o(v);
            const N = s.find(w => w.provider === v);
            c((N == null ? void 0 : N.config) || {})
        },
        y = (v, N) => {
            c(w => ({
                ...w,
                [v]: N
            }))
        },
        g = async () => {
            u(!0);
            try {
                const v = s.find(N => N.provider === i);
                if (!v)
                    return;
                await Ie("PUT", `/api/admin/payment-modules/${i}`, {
                    config: l,
                    isActive: v.isActive
                }),
                t({
                    title: "Configuración guardada",
                    description: "Los cambios se han guardado correctamente"
                }),
                await m()
            } catch {
                t({
                    title: "Error",
                    description: "No se pudo guardar la configuración",
                    variant: "destructive"
                })
            } finally {
                u(!1)
            }
        },
        x = async (v, N) => {
            try {
                const w = s.find(C => C.provider === v);
                if (!w)
                    return;
                await Ie("PUT", `/api/admin/payment-modules/${v}`, {
                    config: w.config,
                    isActive: N
                }),
                t({
                    title: N ? "Módulo activado" : "Módulo desactivado",
                    description: `El módulo ${w.name} ha sido ${N ? "activado" : "desactivado"}`
                }),
                await m()
            } catch {
                t({
                    title: "Error",
                    description: "No se pudo cambiar el estado del módulo",
                    variant: "destructive"
                })
            }
        },
        j = v => {
            switch (v) {
            case "stripe":
                return e.jsx(ps, {
                    className: "w-5 h-5 text-blue-600"
                });
            case "paypal":
                return e.jsx(F5, {
                    className: "w-5 h-5 text-yellow-600"
                });
            case "redsys":
                return e.jsx(ps, {
                    className: "w-5 h-5 text-red-600"
                });
            case "bank_transfer":
                return e.jsx(xf, {
                    className: "w-5 h-5 text-green-600"
                });
            default:
                return e.jsx(Bs, {
                    className: "w-5 h-5"
                })
            }
        },
        b = v => {
            var w;
            const N = l[v.name] || "";
            switch (v.type) {
            case "select":
                return e.jsxs("div", {
                    className: "space-y-2",
                    children: [e.jsxs(q, {
                        htmlFor: v.name,
                        children: [v.label, v.required && e.jsx("span", {
                            className: "text-red-500 ml-1",
                            children: "*"
                        })]
                    }), e.jsxs(He, {
                        value: N,
                        onValueChange: C => y(v.name, C),
                        children: [e.jsx(Ue, {
                            children: e.jsx(We, {
                                placeholder: `Seleccionar ${v.label}`
                            })
                        }), e.jsx(qe, {
                            children: (w = v.options) == null ? void 0 : w.map(C => e.jsx(Q, {
                                value: C.value,
                                children: C.label
                            }, C.value))
                        })]
                    }), v.description && e.jsx("p", {
                        className: "text-sm text-gray-500",
                        children: v.description
                    })]
                }, v.name);
            case "checkbox":
                return e.jsxs("div", {
                    className: "space-y-2",
                    children: [e.jsxs("div", {
                        className: "flex items-center space-x-2",
                        children: [e.jsx(St, {
                            id: v.name,
                            checked: N,
                            onCheckedChange: C => y(v.name, C)
                        }), e.jsx(q, {
                            htmlFor: v.name,
                            children: v.label
                        })]
                    }), v.description && e.jsx("p", {
                        className: "text-sm text-gray-500",
                        children: v.description
                    })]
                }, v.name);
            case "password":
                return e.jsxs("div", {
                    className: "space-y-2",
                    children: [e.jsxs(q, {
                        htmlFor: v.name,
                        children: [v.label, v.required && e.jsx("span", {
                            className: "text-red-500 ml-1",
                            children: "*"
                        })]
                    }), e.jsx(se, {
                        id: v.name,
                        type: "password",
                        value: N,
                        onChange: C => y(v.name, C.target.value),
                        placeholder: `Ingresa ${v.label}`
                    }), v.description && e.jsx("p", {
                        className: "text-sm text-gray-500",
                        children: v.description
                    })]
                }, v.name);
            default:
                return e.jsxs("div", {
                    className: "space-y-2",
                    children: [e.jsxs(q, {
                        htmlFor: v.name,
                        children: [v.label, v.required && e.jsx("span", {
                            className: "text-red-500 ml-1",
                            children: "*"
                        })]
                    }), e.jsx(se, {
                        id: v.name,
                        type: "text",
                        value: N,
                        onChange: C => y(v.name, C.target.value),
                        placeholder: `Ingresa ${v.label}`
                    }), v.description && e.jsx("p", {
                        className: "text-sm text-gray-500",
                        children: v.description
                    })]
                }, v.name)
            }
        };
    if (n)
        return e.jsx("div", {
            className: "flex items-center justify-center h-64",
            children: e.jsx("div", {
                className: "animate-spin w-8 h-8 border-4 border-primary border-t-transparent rounded-full"
            })
        });
    const p = s.find(v => v.provider === i);
    return e.jsxs("div", {
        className: "container mx-auto p-6 space-y-6",
        children: [e.jsxs("div", {
            className: "flex items-center justify-between",
            children: [e.jsx("h1", {
                className: "text-3xl font-bold",
                children: "Módulos de Pago"
            }), e.jsxs(ve, {
                variant: "outline",
                className: "flex items-center gap-2",
                children: [e.jsx(Bs, {
                    className: "w-4 h-4"
                }), "Configuración de Pagos"]
            })]
        }), e.jsxs("div", {
            className: "grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-4 gap-6",
            children: [e.jsxs(V, {
                className: "md:col-span-1",
                children: [e.jsx(ae, {
                    children: e.jsx(ie, {
                        children: "Módulos Disponibles"
                    })
                }), e.jsx(U, {
                    className: "space-y-4",
                    children: s.map(v => e.jsxs("div", {
                        className: `p-3 rounded-lg border cursor-pointer transition-colors ${i === v.provider ? "border-primary bg-primary/10" : "border-gray-200 hover:border-gray-300"}`,
                        onClick: () => f(v.provider),
                        children: [e.jsxs("div", {
                            className: "flex items-center justify-between mb-2",
                            children: [e.jsxs("div", {
                                className: "flex items-center gap-2",
                                children: [j(v.provider), e.jsx("span", {
                                    className: "font-medium",
                                    children: v.name
                                })]
                            }), e.jsxs("div", {
                                className: "flex items-center gap-2",
                                children: [e.jsx(St, {
                                    checked: v.isActive,
                                    onCheckedChange: N => x(v.provider, N),
                                    onClick: N => N.stopPropagation()
                                }), v.isActive ? e.jsx(jp, {
                                    className: "w-4 h-4 text-green-600"
                                }) : e.jsx(er, {
                                    className: "w-4 h-4 text-gray-400"
                                })]
                            })]
                        }), e.jsx(ve, {
                            variant: v.isActive ? "default" : "secondary",
                            className: "text-xs",
                            children: v.isActive ? "Activo" : "Inactivo"
                        })]
                    }, v.provider))
                })]
            }), e.jsxs(V, {
                className: "md:col-span-3",
                children: [e.jsx(ae, {
                    children: e.jsxs(ie, {
                        className: "flex items-center gap-2",
                        children: [p && j(p.provider), "Configuración de ", p == null ? void 0 : p.name]
                    })
                }), e.jsx(U, {
                    children: p ? e.jsxs("div", {
                        className: "space-y-6",
                        children: [e.jsxs("div", {
                            className: "flex items-center gap-2 p-4 bg-blue-50 rounded-lg",
                            children: [e.jsx(zr, {
                                className: "w-5 h-5 text-blue-600"
                            }), e.jsx("p", {
                                className: "text-sm text-blue-800",
                                children: "Configura los parámetros del módulo de pago. Los campos marcados con * son obligatorios."
                            })]
                        }), e.jsx("div", {
                            className: "grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4",
                            children: p.configFields.map(v => b(v))
                        }), e.jsxs("div", {
                            className: "flex justify-end gap-2",
                            children: [e.jsx(M, {
                                variant: "outline",
                                onClick: () => f(i),
                                disabled: d,
                                children: "Descartar Cambios"
                            }), e.jsx(M, {
                                onClick: g,
                                disabled: d,
                                children: d ? "Guardando..." : "Guardar Configuración"
                            })]
                        })]
                    }) : e.jsx("p", {
                        className: "text-center text-gray-500",
                        children: "Selecciona un módulo para configurar"
                    })
                })]
            })]
        }), e.jsxs(V, {
            children: [e.jsx(ae, {
                children: e.jsx(ie, {
                    children: "Información Importante"
                })
            }), e.jsx(U, {
                className: "space-y-4",
                children: e.jsxs("div", {
                    className: "grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4",
                    children: [e.jsxs("div", {
                        className: "space-y-2",
                        children: [e.jsx("h4", {
                            className: "font-semibold",
                            children: "Redsys"
                        }), e.jsx("p", {
                            className: "text-sm text-gray-600",

                        })]
                    }), e.jsxs("div", {
                        className: "space-y-2",
                        children: [e.jsx("h4", {
                            className: "font-semibold",
                            children: "PayPal"
                        }), e.jsx("p", {
                            className: "text-sm text-gray-600",

                        })]
                    }), e.jsxs("div", {
                        className: "space-y-2",
                        children: [e.jsx("h4", {
                            className: "font-semibold",
                            children: "Stripe"
                        }), e.jsx("p", {
                            className: "text-sm text-gray-600",
                            children: "Procesador de pagos con tarjeta. Requiere claves públicas y privadas de Stripe."
                        })]
                    }), e.jsxs("div", {
                        className: "space-y-2",
                        children: [e.jsx("h4", {
                            className: "font-semibold",
                            children: "Transferencia Bancaria"
                        }), e.jsx("p", {
                            className: "text-sm text-gray-600",

                        })]

                })
            })]
        })]
    })
}
const VW = Ae.object({
        name: Ae.string().min(1, "El nombre es requerido"),
        description: Ae.string().optional(),
        base_price: Ae.coerce.number().min(0, "El precio base debe ser mayor o igual a 0"),
        is_active: Ae.boolean().default(!0),
        free_shipping_threshold: Ae.coerce.number().min(0).optional(),
        weight_based_pricing: Ae.boolean().default(!0),
        price_per_kg: Ae.coerce.number().min(0).optional(),
        max_weight: Ae.coerce.number().min(0).optional(),
        estimated_days: Ae.coerce.number().min(1).optional(),
        instructions: Ae.string().optional()
    }),
    UW = Ae.object({
        shipping_config_id: Ae.number(),
        min_weight: Ae.coerce.number().min(0, "El peso mínimo debe ser mayor o igual a 0"),
        max_weight: Ae.coerce.number().optional(),
        price: Ae.coerce.number().min(0, "El precio debe ser mayor o igual a 0")
    }),
    qW = Ae.object({
        name: Ae.string().min(1, "El nombre es requerido"),
        description: Ae.string().optional(),
        sort_order: Ae.coerce.number().min(0, "El orden debe ser mayor o igual a 0"),
        is_active: Ae.boolean().default(!0)
    });

    max_weight: Ae.coerce.number().optional(),
    price: Ae.coerce.number().min(0, "El precio debe ser mayor o igual a 0")
});

                            })

            })]
        })]
    })
}
const HW = () => {
        const {toast: t} = tt(),
            s = hr(),
            [r, n] = h.useState(!1),
            [a, i] = h.useState("config"),
            {data: o, isLoading: l} = _e({
                queryKey: ["/api/admin/email-config"],
                queryFn: async () => {
                    const C = await fetch("/api/admin/email-config");
                    if (!C.ok)
                        throw new Error("Error al cargar configuración de correos");
                    return C.json()
                }
            }),
            {data: c, isLoading: d, refetch: u} = _e({
                queryKey: ["/api/admin/email-logs"],
                queryFn: async () => {
                    const C = await fetch("/api/admin/email-logs?limit=50");
                    if (!C.ok)
                        throw new Error("Error al cargar logs de correos");
                    return C.json()
                },
                enabled: a === "history"
            }),
            m = rt({
                mutationFn: async C => {
                    const E = await fetch("/api/admin/email-config", {
                        method: "POST",
                        headers: {
                            "Content-Type": "application/json"
                        },
                        body: JSON.stringify(C)
                    });
                    if (!E.ok)
                        throw new Error("Error al guardar configuración");
                    return E.json()
                },
                onSuccess: () => {
                    t({
                        title: "Configuración guardada",
                        description: "La configuración de correos se ha guardado correctamente"
                    }),
                    s.invalidateQueries({
                        queryKey: ["/api/admin/email-config"]
                    })
                },
                onError: C => {
                    t({
                        title: "Error",
                        description: "Error al guardar la configuración",
                        variant: "destructive"
                    })
                }
            }),
            f = rt({
                mutationFn: async () => {
                    const C = await fetch("/api/admin/email-config/test", {
                        method: "POST"
                    });
                    if (!C.ok)
                        throw new Error("Error al probar configuración");
                    return C.json()
                },
                onSuccess: () => {
                    t({
                        title: "Prueba exitosa",
                        description: "El correo de prueba se ha enviado correctamente"
                    }),
                    a === "history" && u()
                },
                onError: C => {
                    t({
                        title: "Error en la prueba",
                        description: "Error al enviar el correo de prueba",
                        variant: "destructive"
                    })
                }
            }),
            y = rt({
                mutationFn: async C => {
                    const E = await fetch(`/api/admin/email-logs/${C}`, {
                        method: "DELETE"
                    });
                    if (!E.ok)
                        throw new Error("Error al eliminar log");
                    return E.json()
                },
                onSuccess: () => {
                    t({
                        title: "Log eliminado",
                        description: "El log se ha eliminado correctamente"
                    }),
                    u()
                },
                onError: C => {
                    t({
                        title: "Error",
                        description: "Error al eliminar el log",
                        variant: "destructive"
                    })
                }
            }),
            g = rt({
                mutationFn: async () => {
                    const C = await fetch("/api/admin/email-logs", {
                        method: "DELETE"
                    });
                    if (!C.ok)
                        throw new Error("Error al limpiar historial");
                    return C.json()
                },
                onSuccess: () => {
                    t({
                        title: "Historial limpiado",
                        description: "Todo el historial de correos se ha eliminado"
                    }),
                    u()
                },
                onError: C => {
                    t({
                        title: "Error",
                        description: "Error al limpiar el historial",
                        variant: "destructive"
                    })
                }
            }),
            x = (C, E) => {
                m.mutate({
                    key: C,
                    value: E
                })
            },
            j = async () => {
                n(!0);
                try {
                    await f.mutateAsync()
                } finally {
                    n(!1)
                }
            },
            b = C => {
                const E = o == null ? void 0 : o.find(k => k.key === C);
                return (E == null ? void 0 : E.value) || ""
            },
            p = C => {
                const E = o == null ? void 0 : o.find(k => k.key === C);
                return (E == null ? void 0 : E.isActive) || !1
            },
            v = C => new Date(C).toLocaleString("es-ES", {
                year: "numeric",
                month: "short",
                day: "numeric",
                hour: "2-digit",
                minute: "2-digit"
            }),
            N = C => {
                switch (C) {
                case "sent":
                    return e.jsx(ve, {
                        variant: "default",
                        className: "bg-green-100 text-green-800",
                        children: "Enviado"
                    });
                case "failed":
                    return e.jsx(ve, {
                        variant: "destructive",
                        children: "Error"
                    });
                case "pending":
                    return e.jsx(ve, {
                        variant: "secondary",
                        children: "Pendiente"
                    });
                default:
                    return e.jsx(ve, {
                        variant: "outline",
                        children: C
                    })
                }
            },
            w = C => {
                switch (C) {
                case "contact_form":
                    return "Formulario de contacto";
                case "order_confirmation":
                    return "Confirmación de pedido";
                case "order_notification":
                    return "Notificación de pedido";

                    return "Prueba";

                    return C
                }
            };

            [n, a] = h.useState(!1),
            [i, o] = h.useState({
                id: "1",
                bannerEnabled: !0,
                bannerMessage: "Utilizamos cookies para mejorar tu experiencia en nuestro sitio web. Al continuar navegando, aceptas nuestro uso de cookies.",

                    await new Promise(m => setTimeout(m, 1e3)),

                        title: "Configuración guardada",
                        description: "La configuración de cookies se ha guardado correctamente."
                    })

                    t({
                        title: "Error al guardar",

                                                }) : e.jsx(Ea, {
                                                    className: "ml-2 h-4 w-4 text-red-500"
                                                })]
                                            }), e.jsxs("div", {
                                                className: "flex gap-2",

                                                    variant: "outline",

                                                    children: "Exportar JSON"

                                                    variant: "outline",

                                                    children: "Exportar CSV"
                                                })]
                                            })]
                                        }), H.error ? e.jsx("div", {
                                            className: "bg-red-50 text-red-500 p-3 rounded-md overflow-x-auto",
                                            children: e.jsx("pre", {
                                                className: "text-xs",
                                                children: H.error
                                            })
                                        }) : e.jsx("div", {
                                            className: "bg-muted p-3 rounded-md overflow-x-auto max-h-96",
                                            children: e.jsx("pre", {
                                                className: "text-xs",
                                                children: JSON.stringify(H.response, null, 2)
                                            })
                                        })]
                                    })]
                                }, H.id))
                            })
                        })]
                    })
                }, z.id))]
            })]
        })]
    })
}

function nG() {
    const t = Date.now().toString(36),
        s = Math.random().toString(36).substring(2, 15);

function yy() {

function aG() {
    const {toast: t} = tt(),
        {items: s, clearCart: r, setItems: n} = Nl(),
        [, a] = dt(),

        [l, c] = h.useState([]),

        [m, f] = h.useState(!0),

        [b, p] = h.useState(!1),
        [v, N] = h.useState("guest"),
        [w, C] = h.useState(""),
        [E, k] = h.useState(""),

        [z, H] = h.useState(null),
        [F, A] = h.useState(!1),
        [P, I] = h.useState({
            customerName: "",
            customerLastName: "",
            customerEmail: "",
            customerPhone: "",
            shippingAddress: "",
            shippingCity: "",
            shippingProvince: "",
            shippingPostalCode: "",
            billingAddress: "",
            billingCity: "",
            billingProvince: "",
            billingPostalCode: "",
            useSameAddress: !0,
            paymentMethodId: "",
            shippingMethodId: "",
            notes: "",
            createAccount: !1,
            password: ""
        });
    h.useEffect(() => {
        if (ne(), $(), s.length === 0) {
            const T = sessionStorage.getItem("backup_cart_data");
            if (T)
                try {
                    const te = JSON.parse(T);
                    Array.isArray(te) && te.length > 0 && (console.log("🔄 Restaurando carrito desde backup en checkout:", te.length, "items"), n(te), sessionStorage.removeItem("backup_cart_data"))
                } catch (te) {
                    console.error("Error restaurando carrito en checkout:", te)
                }
        }
    }, []),
    h.useEffect(() => {
        P.shippingProvince && s.length > 0 && O()
    }, [P.shippingProvince, s]);
    const $ = async () => {
            try {
                const T = await fetch("/api/auth/me", {
                    credentials: "include"
                });
                if (T.ok) {
                    const te = await T.json();
                    R(te);

                        credentials: "include"
                    });
                    if (W.ok) {
                        const re = await W.json();
                        H(re)
                    }
                    te && (I(re => ({
                        ...re,
                        customerName: te.firstName || "",
                        customerLastName: te.lastName || "",
                        customerEmail: te.email || "",
                        customerPhone: te.phone || "",
                        shippingAddress: te.address || "",
                        shippingCity: te.city || "",
                        shippingProvince: te.province || "",
                        shippingPostalCode: te.postalCode || "",
                        billingAddress: te.billingAddress || te.address || "",
                        billingCity: te.billingCity || te.city || "",
                        billingProvince: te.billingProvince || te.province || "",
                        billingPostalCode: te.billingPostalCode || te.postalCode || "",

            }
        },

                    W = await T.json(),

                o(W),

                }))
            } catch (T) {

                })

        },
        O = async () => {
            if (!(!P.shippingProvince || s.length === 0)) {
                p(!0),
                console.log(`🚚 Calculando envío para ${s.length} items distintos:`),
                s.forEach(T => {
                    console.log(`  - ID: ${T.partId}, Código: ${T.partCode}, Cantidad: ${T.quantity}, Peso almacenado: ${T.partWeight}g`)
                });
                try {
                    const T = await Promise.all(s.map(async re => {
                        let de = re.partWeight;
                        if (console.log(`Pieza ${re.partId} (${re.partCode}) - peso almacenado: ${de}g`), !de || de === 500)
                            try {
                                let me = await fetch(`/api/parts/${re.partId}`),
                                    ye = null;
                                if (me.ok)
                                    ye = await me.json();
                                else if (re.partCode && (console.log(`Buscando pieza por código: ${re.partCode}`), me = await fetch(`/api/search-parts?search=${encodeURIComponent(re.partCode)}&limit=1`), me.ok)) {
                                    const lt = await me.json();
                                    lt.data && lt.data.length > 0 && (ye = lt.data[0], console.log(`Encontrada pieza por código ${re.partCode}: ID ${ye.id}, peso ${ye.peso}g`))
                                }
                                if (ye) {
                                    const lt = ye.peso ? parseInt(ye.peso.toString()) : null;
                                    console.log(`Pieza ${re.partId} - peso de API: ${lt}g`),
                                    de = lt || 500
                                } else
                                    console.log(`Pieza ${re.partId} - no encontrada, usando 500g por defecto`),
                                    de = 500
                            } catch (me) {
                                console.error("Error fetching part weight:", me),
                                de = 500
                            }
                        const le = de * re.quantity;
                        return console.log(`Pieza ${re.partId} - peso final: ${de}g × ${re.quantity} = ${le}g`), {

                        }

                    throw new Error("Método de pago no seleccionado");

                        },

                        if (ye.success) {
                            sessionStorage.setItem("pending_order_data", JSON.stringify(de)),
                            window.location.href = `${ye.data.redirectUrl}&session_id=${re}`;
                            return
                        }
                    }

                    const le = {
                            amount: parseFloat(de.total),
                            currency: "EUR",
                            description: "Pedido - Desguace Murcia",

                            window.location.href = `${ye.data.redirectUrl}&session_id=${re}`;
                            return
                        }
                    }
                } else if (W.provider === "redsys") {
                    sessionStorage.setItem("backup_cart_data", JSON.stringify(s));

                    if (le.ok) {

                                id: me.id,

                                customerEmail: de.customerEmail,
                                customerName: `${de.customerName} ${de.customerLastName}`,

                                cancelUrl: `${window.location.origin}/checkout?error=payment_cancelled`,
                                metadata: {
                                    orderId: me.id
                                }
                            },

                        if (lt.ok) {
                            const ut = await lt.json();
                            if (ut.success && ut.data.formHtml) {
                                console.log("🚨 CHECKOUT DEBUG - Enviando directamente a Redsys:", {
                                    success: ut.success,
                                    hasFormHtml: !!ut.data.formHtml,
                                    actionUrl: ut.data.actionUrl,
                                    orderNumber: ut.data.orderNumber,
                                    redsysOrderNumber: ut.data.redsysOrderNumber,
                                    amount: ut.data.amount
                                });
                                const bt = document.createElement("div"),

                                bt.innerHTML = G,
                                bt.style.display = "none",

                        })]

                })
            })]
        })
    })

            })]
        })
    };

        [, r] = dt(),

        [i, o] = h.useState(!0),
        [l, c] = h.useState("");
    h.useEffect(() => {
        d();
        const y = new URLSearchParams(window.location.search);
        c(y.get("payment") || "")
    }, [t.orderId]);
    const d = async () => {
        try {
            const g = new URLSearchParams(window.location.search).get("sessionId"),
                x = yy(),
                j = g || x;
            let b = `/api/orders/${t.orderId}`;
            j && (b += `?sessionId=${j}`);
            const p = await Ie("GET", b);
            if (p.ok) {
                const v = await p.json();
                a(v)
            } else
                s({
                    title: "Error",
                    description: "No se pudo cargar la información del pedido",
                    variant: "destructive"
                })
        } catch (y) {
            console.error("Error loading order:", y),
            s({
                title: "Error",
                description: "No se pudo cargar la información del pedido",
                variant: "destructive"
            })
        } finally {
            o(!1)
        }
    };
    if (i)
        return e.jsx("div", {
            className: "container mx-auto px-4 py-8",

                className: "text-center",

        });

            })]
        })
    })

const uG = Ae.object({
        identifier: Ae.string().min(3, "Ingresa un email o nombre de usuario válido"),
        password: Ae.string().min(6, "La contraseña debe tener al menos 6 caracteres")
    }),
    mG = () => {
        const {login: t, isLoading: s} = _s(),

    return function() {
        return t.apply(s, arguments)
    }
}

}

function Mm(t, s, {allOwnKeys: r=!1}={}) {
    if (t === null || typeof t > "u")
        return;
    let n,
        a;
    if (typeof t != "object" && (t = [t]), id(t))
        for (n = 0, a = t.length; n < a; n++)
            s.call(null, t[n], n, t);
    else {
        const i = r ? Object.getOwnPropertyNames(t) : Object.keys(t),
            o = i.length;
        let l;
        for (n = 0; n < o; n++)
            l = i[n],
            s.call(null, t[l], l, t)
    }
}
function bM(t, s) {
    s = s.toLowerCase();
    const r = Object.keys(t);
    let n = r.length,
        a;
    for (; n-- > 0;)
        if (a = r[n], s === a.toLowerCase())
            return a;

function WK(t, s, r) {

        throw new ht("options must be an object", ht.ERR_BAD_OPTION_VALUE);

    let a = n.length;

            o = s[i];

                c = l === void 0 || o(l, i, t);
            if (c !== !0)
                throw new ht("option " + i + " must be " + c, ht.ERR_BAD_OPTION_VALUE);
            continue
        }
        if (r !== !0)
            throw new ht("Unknown option " + i, ht.ERR_BAD_OPTION)
    }
}

class Zo {
    constructor(s)
    {
        this.defaults = s || {},

            request: new Y1,
            response: new Y1
        }
    }
    async request(s, r)
    {
        try {
            return await this._request(s, r)
        } catch (n) {
            if (n instanceof Error) {
                let a = {};
                Error.captureStackTrace ? Error.captureStackTrace(a) : a = new Error;
                const i = a.stack ? a.stack.replace(/^.+\n/, "") : "";
                try {
                    n.stack ? i && !String(n.stack).endsWith(i.replace(/^.+\n.+\n/, "")) && (n.stack += `
`
                    + i) : n.stack = i
                } catch {}
            }
            throw n
        }
    }
    _request(s, r)
    {
        typeof s == "string" ? (r = r || {}, r.url = s) : r = s || {},
        r = xl(this.defaults, r);
        const {transitional: n, paramsSerializer: a, headers: i} = r;

            silentJSONParsing: la.transitional(la.boolean),

        }, !1),
        a != null && (ce.isFunction(a) ? r.paramsSerializer = {
            serialize: a
        } : Vh.assertOptions(a, {
            encode: la.function,
            serialize: la.function
        }, !0)),
        r.allowAbsoluteUrls !== void 0 || (this.defaults.allowAbsoluteUrls !== void 0 ? r.allowAbsoluteUrls = this.defaults.allowAbsoluteUrls : r.allowAbsoluteUrls = !0),
        Vh.assertOptions(r, {
            baseUrl: la.spelling("baseURL"),
            withXsrfToken: la.spelling("withXSRFToken")
        }, !0),
        r.method = (r.method || this.defaults.method || "get").toLowerCase();
        let o = i && ce.merge(i.common, i[r.method]);
        i && ce.forEach(["delete", "get", "head", "post", "put", "patch", "common"], g => {
            delete i[g]
        }),
        r.headers = Kr.concat(o, i);
        const l = [];
        let c = !0;
        this.interceptors.request.forEach(function(x) {
            typeof x.runWhen == "function" && x.runWhen(r) === !1 || (c = c && x.synchronous, l.unshift(x.fulfilled, x.rejected))
        });
        const d = [];

        });

                u = u.then(g[m++], g[m++]);
            return u
        }
        f = l.length;

                x = l[m++];

            } catch (j) {
                x.call(this, j);

            }
        }

        } catch (g) {
            return Promise.reject(g)
        }
        for (m = 0, f = d.length; m < f;)
            u = u.then(d[m++], d[m++]);
        return u
    }
    getUri(s)
    {
        s = xl(this.defaults, s);
        const r = IM(s.baseURL, s.url, s.allowAbsoluteUrls);

class gb {
    constructor(s)
    {
        if (typeof s != "function")
            throw new TypeError("executor must be a function.");
        let r;
        this.promise = new Promise(function(i) {
            r = i
        });
        const n = this;
        this.promise.then(a => {
            if (!n._listeners)
                return;
            let i = n._listeners.length;
            for (; i-- > 0;)
                n._listeners[i](a);
            n._listeners = null
        }),
        this.promise.then = a => {
            let i;
            const o = new Promise(l => {
                n.subscribe(l),
                i = l
            }).then(a);
            return o.cancel = function() {
                n.unsubscribe(i)
            }, o
        },
        s(function(i, o, l) {
            n.reason || (n.reason = new od(i, o, l), r(n.reason))
        })
    }
    throwIfRequested()
    {
        if (this.reason)
            throw this.reason
    }
    subscribe(s)
    {
        if (this.reason) {
            s(this.reason);
            return
        }
        this._listeners ? this._listeners.push(s) : this._listeners = [s]
    }
    unsubscribe(s)
    {
        if (!this._listeners)
            return;
        const r = this._listeners.indexOf(s);
        r !== -1 && this._listeners.splice(r, 1)
    }
    toAbortSignal()
    {
        const s = new AbortController,
            r = n => {
                s.abort(n)
            };
        return this.subscribe(r), s.signal.unsubscribe = () => this.unsubscribe(r), s.signal
    }
    static source()
    {
        let s;
        return {
            token: new gb(function(a) {
                s = a
            }),
            cancel: s
        }
    }
}

                                })]

                                        }), e.jsx(se, {

                                        }), e.jsx("p", {
                                            className: "text-sm text-gray-500",
                                            children: "El sistema buscará vehículos compatibles basados en los campos de matching de la pieza (codVersion, puertas, anyoInicio, anyoFin, rvCode)."

                                    })
                                })
                            }), e.jsx(_a, {
                                className: "flex justify-end",
                                children: e.jsx(M, {
                                    onClick: b,
                                    disabled: s,
                                    children: s ? "Buscando..." : "Buscar vehículos compatibles"
                                })
                            })]
                        }), e.jsxs(V, {
                            children: [e.jsxs(ae, {
                                children: [e.jsx(ie, {
                                    children: "Vehículos Compatibles"
                                }), e.jsx(qt, {
                                    children: "Aquí se mostrarán los vehículos compatibles con la pieza"
                                })]
                            }), e.jsx(U, {
                                children: i ? e.jsxs("div", {
                                    className: "space-y-4",
                                    children: [e.jsxs("div", {
                                        className: "p-4 rounded-md bg-gray-50",
                                        children: [e.jsx("p", {
                                            className: "font-semibold",
                                            children: i.success ? e.jsxs("span", {
                                                className: "text-green-600",
                                                children: ["✓ Se encontraron ", i.count, " vehículos compatibles"]
                                            }) : e.jsx("span", {
                                                className: "text-red-600",
                                                children: "✗ No se encontraron vehículos compatibles"
                                            })
                                        }), i.success && i.data && i.data.length > 0 && e.jsxs("div", {
                                            className: "mt-4",
                                            children: [e.jsx("p", {
                                                className: "font-semibold mb-2",
                                                children: "Vehículos compatibles:"
                                            }), e.jsx("div", {
                                                className: "max-h-64 overflow-y-auto",
                                                children: i.data.map((v, N) => e.jsxs("div", {
                                                    className: "mb-4 p-3 bg-white rounded border border-gray-200",
                                                    children: [e.jsxs("p", {
                                                        className: "text-sm text-gray-500",
                                                        children: ["Vehículo #", N + 1]
                                                    }), e.jsxs("p", {
                                                        children: [e.jsx("span", {
                                                            className: "font-semibold",
                                                            children: "ID:"
                                                        }), " ", v.id]
                                                    }), e.jsxs("p", {
                                                        children: [e.jsx("span", {
                                                            className: "font-semibold",
                                                            children: "Marca:"
                                                        }), " ", v.marca]
                                                    }), e.jsxs("p", {
                                                        children: [e.jsx("span", {
                                                            className: "font-semibold",
                                                            children: "Modelo:"
                                                        }), " ", v.modelo]
                                                    }), e.jsxs("p", {
                                                        children: [e.jsx("span", {
                                                            className: "font-semibold",
                                                            children: "Versión:"
                                                        }), " ", v.version]
                                                    }), e.jsxs("p", {
                                                        children: [e.jsx("span", {
                                                            className: "font-semibold",
                                                            children: "Año:"
                                                        }), " ", v.anyo]
                                                    })]
                                                }, v.id))
                                            })]
                                        }), !i.success && e.jsx("p", {
                                            className: "mt-2",
                                            children: "No se encontraron vehículos compatibles con la pieza proporcionada."
                                        })]
                                    }), e.jsxs("div", {
                                        children: [e.jsx("p", {
                                            className: "text-sm font-semibold mb-1",
                                            children: "Datos de respuesta completos:"
                                        }), e.jsx("pre", {
                                            className: "p-2 bg-gray-100 rounded-md overflow-auto text-xs",
                                            children: JSON.stringify(i, null, 2)
                                        })]
                                    })]
                                }) : e.jsx("div", {
                                    className: "flex justify-center items-center h-48 text-gray-400",
                                    children: "Aquí se mostrarán los vehículos compatibles"
                                })
                            })]
                        })]
                    })]
                })
            })]
        })]
    })
}
function YK() {
    const [t, s] = h.useState(null),
        [r, n] = h.useState(!0);
    return h.useEffect(() => {
        (async () => {
            try {
                console.log("TEST: Cargando módulos de pago...");
                const i = await fetch("/api/admin/payment-modules");
                console.log("TEST: Response status:", i.status),
                console.log("TEST: Response ok:", i.ok);
                const o = await i.json();
                console.log("TEST: Data received:", o),
                console.log("TEST: Data type:", typeof o),
                console.log("TEST: Is array?", Array.isArray(o)),
                Array.isArray(o) && (console.log("TEST: Data length:", o.length), console.log("TEST: First module:", o[0])),
                s(o),
                n(!1)
            } catch (i) {
                console.error("TEST: Error:", i),
                s({
                    error: i.message
                }),
                n(!1)
            }
        })()
    }, []), r ? e.jsxs("div", {
        style: {
            padding: "20px"
        },
        children: [e.jsx("h1", {
            children: "Test Payment Modules"
        }), e.jsx("p", {
            children: "Loading..."
        })]
    }) : e.jsxs("div", {
        style: {
            padding: "20px"
        },
        children: [e.jsx("h1", {
            children: "Test Payment Modules"
        }), t && t.error ? e.jsxs("div", {
            style: {
                color: "red"
            },
            children: [e.jsx("h2", {
                children: "Error!"
            }), e.jsx("p", {
                children: t.error
            })]
        }) : Array.isArray(t) ? e.jsxs("div", {
            style: {
                color: "green"
            },
            children: [e.jsx("h2", {
                children: "Success!"
            }), e.jsxs("p", {
                children: ["Modules loaded: ", t.length]
            }), e.jsx("pre", {
                style: {
                    background: "#f0f0f0",
                    padding: "10px",
                    overflow: "auto"
                },
                children: JSON.stringify(t, null, 2)
            })]
        }) : e.jsxs("div", {
            style: {
                color: "orange"
            },
            children: [e.jsx("h2", {
                children: "Unexpected data type"
            }), e.jsx("p", {
                children: "Data is not an array"
            }), e.jsx("pre", {
                style: {
                    background: "#f0f0f0",
                    padding: "10px",
                    overflow: "auto"
                },
                children: JSON.stringify(t, null, 2)
            })]
        })]
    })
}

function _t({path: t, component: s}) {
    const {user: r, isLoading: n} = _s();
    return n ? e.jsx(Nt, {
        path: t,

                className: "h-8 w-8 animate-spin text-border"
            })
        })
    }) : r ? e.jsx(Nt, {
        path: t,
        component: s
    }) : e.jsx(Nt, {
        path: t,
        children: () => e.jsx(ZS, {
            to: "/login"
        })
    })
}

                        throw new Error("Error al generar el feed");

                    document.body.appendChild(j),
